<center><p>
<hr width="100%" ><font COLOR="#000080"><font SIZE=+3>REGIONAL SEMINAR
ON THE</font></font></p></center>

<center><p><b><font COLOR="#000080"><font SIZE=+3>CHEMICAL WEAPONS CONVENTION</font></font></b></p></center>

<center><p><font COLOR="#000080"><font SIZE=+3>AND ITS NATIONAL IMPLEMENTATION
</font></font>
<hr width="100%" ></p></center>

<center><p><font COLOR="#95004A"><font SIZE=+2>12 - 14 JUNE 1996, MALTA</font></font></p></center>

<center><p><font COLOR="#95004A"><b><tt><font SIZE=+2>OUTLINE OF A TENTATIVE
PROGRAMME</font></tt></b> </font>
<hr width="100%" ></p></center>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>WEDNESDAY, 12 JUNE 1996</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>09.00 Inaugural Session</font></b></p>

<ul>
<p><font SIZE=+1>Chairman and Moderator: </font></p>

<p><font SIZE=+1>Mr. Saviour F. Borg, Director Multilateral Affairs, Ministry
of Foreign Affairs</font></p>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Keynote speech by the Executive Secretary of the Preparatory
Commission, Mr Ian R. Kenyon.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Welcome address by Minister for Gozo, Mr. Anton Tabone.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Opening of the Seminar by H. E. Guido de Marco, Deputy
Prim Minister and Ministar of Foreign Affairs, Malta</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Welcome reception</font></li>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>11:00 Introductory Plenary Session</font></b></p>

<ul>
<li><font SIZE=+1>Background to the Chemical Weapons Convention.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>The work of the Commission until June 1996.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>National statements</font></li>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>13:00 Break</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>14:30 - 18:00 Afternoon session</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>14:30 Legislation required to meet the basic undertakings
under the CWC</font></b></p>

<ul>
<li><font SIZE=+1>Existing Legislations</font></li>

