<li><font SIZE=+1>National preparations for receiving inspections</font></li>

<ul>
<li><font SIZE=+1>industry inspections</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>challenge inspections</font></li>
</ul>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Operational tasks relating to declarations</font></li>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>12:30 Break</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>14:30 - 18:00 Afternoon Session</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>14:30 Issues relating to trade in scheduled chemicals</font></b></p>

<ul>
<p><font SIZE=+1>Moderator:</font></p>

<li><font SIZE=+1>The legal framework for collecting import/export data.
National examples.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>The role of the customs authorities in data collection.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Transhipments of scheduled chemicals - political and
practical impact.</font></li>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>20:00 Reception hosted by Minister for Gozo, Mr. Anton
Tabone.</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>FRIDAY, 14 JUNE 1996</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>09:00 - 12:00 Morning Session</font></b></p>

