<H1>REPORT OF THE COLLOQUIUM ON NEUTRALITY AND NON-ALIGNMENT</H1>

<P>
<B>NOVEMBER 4-8, 1991</B>
<H2>INTRODUCTION</H2>

<P>
This Colloquium was convened by the Mediterranean Academy of Diplomatic
Studies and the Graduate Institute of International Studies in
Geneva to consider the impact of recent events and forseeable
future developments on the concepts on neutrality and non-alignment
and their implementation in State practice. Although over a year
has passed since the Colloquium took place, its debates and conclusions
have in no way been contradicted by what happened since. Indeed
much of the neutrality discussions currently under way in relation
with accession negotiations to the European Community with Austria,
Finland and Sweden closely reflect what was found in a more academic
context during the Colloquium.
<P>
<B>Dietrich Kappeler</B>
