<html> <head>
<title>EMISAR</title>
</head>

<body>
<h1>EMISAR</h1>

EMISAR is a dual frequency (L- and C-band) fully polarimetric (4 complex channels per frequency) Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) system developed for remote sensing applications. The system has also an interferometric mode for topographic application which is still experimental.
 
The system is used for DRCS applications but is also available for scientific partners and, to a limited extend, also for customers. The latter may contact E. Lintz Christensen (<a href="mailto:Lintz@emi.dtu.dk">Lintz@emi.dtu.dk</a>) for further information on costs and availability.<br>
<br>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="http://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/emisar-background.html">Background</a><br>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="http://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/Diagram_1b.GIF">EMISAR System Overview</a><br>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="http://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/emisar-system.html">SAR System Description</a><br>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="http://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/Parameters-b.GIF">EMISAR System Parameters</a><br>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="http://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/Diagram_2b.GIF">EMISAR Block Diagram</a><br>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="http://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/images/JD_geology.jpeg">Sample image.</a><br>



