<html> <head>
<title>Aerodynamic Roughness</title>
</head>

<body>
<center><h1>Aerodynamic Roughness</h1></center>
<p>
<b>Science partner</b>: Henrik Sgaard, Institute of Geography,
<a href="http://www.ku.dk/welcome-e.html">University of Copenhagen.</a><br>
<P>
<b>DCRS contact</b>: <a href="//ms/DCRS/staff/kw.html">Kim Woelders</a>, e-mail: <a href="mailto:kw@emi.dtu.dk">kw@emi.dtu.dk</a><br>
<p>
The aerodynamic roughness is
an important parameter when modelling vertical transport of heat,
water vapour, and mass since areas with large aerodynamic roughness
will create more turbulence and thereby vertical transport. This
work aims at investigating the use of SAR techniques to determine
aerodynamic roughness from aircraft or satellites, particularly
in vegetated areas.
<p>

<!-- <b>Project related data</b>: <a href="">Click here</a> (requires password). -->
<p>

<hr>
<address><a href="//www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/staff/bbt.html">Bjorn B. Thomsen &lt;bbt@emi.dtu.dk&gt;</a></address>
