<html> <head>
<title>Plant and Soil Mapping</title>
</head>

<body>
<center><a  href="/images/pm005_m14_foulum_chh.gif"><IMG SRC="/images/pm005_m14_foulum_chh.gif" border=0></a>
<h1>Plant and Soil Mapping</h1></center>
<P>
<b>Science partner</b>: Anton Thomsen, Danish Institute of Plant and
Soil Science, Research Centre Foulum (RCF).
<p>
<b>DCRS contact</b>: <a href="//www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/staff/hs.html">Henning Skriver</a>, e-mail: <a href="mailto:hs@emi.dtu.dk">hs@emi.dtu.dk</a><br>
<p>
This research concerns
the application of radar remote sensing techniques to monitor
agricultural crops, biomass, and soil physics. The observational
techniques includes SAR polarimetry and interferometry, as well
as low frequency radiometry to measure soil moisture content.
The applicability of these observational techniques to research
on crop micro meteorology, hydrology, and forestry will also be
investigated. A key component of this study is multi temporal
data collection near RCF. RCF includes 700 ha of intensively monitored
farm land which is an ideal test site for the application of remote
sensing to agriculture. Even larger areas at the neighbouring
Tjele Estate, is also well mapped and closely monitored.

<p>
<!-- <b>Project related data</b>: <a href="">Click here</a> (requires password). -->
<p>


