<html> <head>
<title>Landscape Ecology</title>
</head>

<body>
<center><a  href="/images/pm005_m14_foulum_chh.gif"><IMG SRC="/images/pm005_m14_foulum_chh.gif" border=0></a>
<h1>Landscape Ecology</h1></center>
<P>
<b>Science partner</b>: John Tychsen, National Environmental Research Institute (<a href="http://www.dmu.dk">NERI</a>). 
<p>
<b>DCRS contact</b>: <a href="//www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/staff/hs.html">Henning Skriver</a>, e-mail: <a href="mailto:hs@emi.dtu.dk">hs@emi.dtu.dk</a><br>
<p>
This is a study of the use of high resolution polarimetric
synthetic aperture radar techniques to map and monitor landscape
patterns, as well as seasonal and man-made changes. The aim is
to develop observation techniques, data processing and interpretation
methods which will allow fast and efficient assessment of the
state of the land environment, vegetation, and also the conditions
for biological life.

<p>
<!-- <b>Project related data</b>: <a href="">Click here</a> (requires password). -->
<p>

