<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>R 631, July, 1996</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.jw.estec.esa.nl:8080/emac/emac95.html"><B>EMAC-95</B></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>The European Multi-sensor Airborne Campaign (EMAC-94/95)
is a programme providing support for the preparation of future
satellite remote sensing programmes and their users.</FONT> 
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>The EMAC-95 campaign concentrated on snow and ice
experiments in northern Europe. In addition, the EMAC-94 flights
associated with the NOrthern hemisphere climate Processes land-surface
Experiment (NOPEX) at Uppsala, Sweden, were continued.</FONT>
<P>
<B>EMISAR Deployment in the EMAC-95 Campaign</B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Four airborne sensors were used in 1995, viz. the
<A HREF="http://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/emisar.html">EMISAR</A> and
ESAR imaging radars, and the HUT and UKMO microwave radiometers.
On campaigns in March, May, and July EMISAR collected fully polarimetric
L- and C- band data from the three ice and snow sites as well
as the NOPEX site; a total of 46 polarimetric scenes. The data
collection was carried out as planned.</FONT> 
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>The EMISAR calibration procedure relies on an internal
calibration system which greatly relieves the dependence on external
calibration targets. For the calibration verification and long
term stability the internal calibration is complemented by corrections
derived from external calibration experiments. Therefore, on each
of the three campaigns the Danish calibration site at Foulum was
mapped at both L-band and C-band. The corrections to the internal
calibration are small and very similar from mission to mission.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>An analysis of the internal calibration data has
proven that the EMISAR stability during mapping is fully satisfactory.
Also, an analysis of the focused and calibrated Foulum scenes
has confirmed that the map to map calibration stability is actually
sufficient for using just a single external calibration per mission.
As a matter of fact, the results indicate that external calibration
is barely necessary on every mission, however, it is still desired
as a means to confirm the expected calibration performance.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>The raw data have been focused and a polarimetric
calibration has been applied. The deliverables include Exabyte
tapes with two data products: 1) the full resolution scattering
matrix data in the slant range projection and 2) the multi-looked
covariance matrix data in the pseudo ground range projection.
'Pseudo' refers to the fact that the projection has not taken
into account the terrain elevation.</FONT> 
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>All March and July data were delivered mid November,
1995, and the May data were delivered in the period February to
June 1996. To begin with the delivery was tentatively scheduled
for October 1, but the processing was delayed by 1) run-in of
the L-band system which had only been flown twice prior to the
EMAC-95 campaigns, 2) introduction of the covariance matrix format,
and 3) multiple HDDT recorder break downs. Additionally, the processing
of the May data was delayed by the fact that the HDDT tapes used
in May turned out to be bad, although certified by Ampex. Finally,
the processing of two scenes delivered in June was postponed because
it was not clear if they should be processed at all. The two scenes
are from the Finnish Ice site, but they did virtually not cover
any ice.</FONT> 
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/emac/emac-95exeps.ps">EMAC-95 report</A> (22 pages)
<LI><A HREF="http://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/emac/emac-95_ipr.ps">Impulse Responses</A> (2 pages)
<LI><A HREF="http://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/emac/emac-95_xtalk.ps">Cross Talk</A> (1 page)
<LI><A HREF="http://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/DCRS/emac/emac-95_appc.ps">Appendix C - read_me files</A> (47 pages)
<LI><A HREF="http://www.jw.estec.esa.nl:8080/emac/emac95.html">EMISAR images</A>
</UL>
</BODY>
