<html> <head>
<title>SAR Polarimetry</title>
</head>

<body>

<center>
<!-- <a  href=""><IMG SRC="/images/" border=0></a> -->
 <h1>SAR Polarimetry</h1>
</center>

<P>
<b>DCRS contact</b>: <a href="//megasat.emi.dtu.dk/DCRS/staff/elc.html">Erik Lintz Christensen</a>, e-mail: <a href="mailto:elc@emi.dtu.dk">elc@emi.dtu.dk</a> and
<a href="//megasat.emi.dtu.dk/DCRS/staff/jd.html">Jrgen Dall</a>, e-mail: <a href="mailto:jd@emi.dtu.dk">jd@emi.dtu.dk</a><br>
<P>
The SAR research is based on the state-of-the-art C-band fully
polarimetric SAR developed at EMI with support from the EU's Joint
Research Centre, operated on a Danish Air Force Gulfstream G-3
aircraft. A longer wavelength L-band system was tested
early 1995. The technology program includes processing,
calibration, analysis and tools for analysing polarimetric SAR
data including polarisation signatures, calculating optimal polarimetric
classifiers, performing polarimetric decomposition, map transformations
etc. This activity also includes maintenance of the polarimetric
SAR system, tests, engineering and calibration flights, and verification
of the overall sensor system and data quality.

<hr>
<address><a href="/DCRS/staff/bbt.html">Bjorn B. Thomsen &lt;bbt@emi.dtu.dk&gt;</a></address>
