<html> <head>
<title>SAR Interferometry</title>
</head>

<body>

<center>
<!-- <a  href=""><IMG SRC="/images/" border=0></a> -->
 <h1>SAR Interferometry</h1>
</center>

<P>
<b>DCRS contact</b>: <a href="/DCRS/staff/snm.html">Sren Nrvang Madsen</a>, e-mail: <a href="mailto:snm@emi.dtu.dk">snm@emi.dtu.dk</a><br>
<p>
During 1995 the SAR has been upgraded to include interferometric
modes, which enables 3-dimensional data collection and measurement
on velocity fields. The polarimetric SAR installation on the G-3
has been augmented with additional C-band flush mounted antennas
displaced cross track. A state-of-the-art navigation and attitude
systems (tightly coupled INU/GPS) is integrated to provide
accurate measurements of aircraft motion and attitude. Also, a
unique capability has been developed that allows the radar to
steer the aircraft based on real-time GPS positions and velocities
thus providing the capability to accurately design the track geometry
for repeat track interferometry.

<hr>
<address><a href="/DCRS/staff/bbt.html">Bjorn B. Thomsen &lt;bbt@emi.dtu.dk&gt;</a></address>
<!-- hhmts start -->
