<html> <head>
<title>Satellite Sensors and Computational Tools</title>
</head>

<body>
<center>
<!-- <a  href=""><IMG SRC="/images/" border=0></a> -->
<h1>Satellite Sensors and Computational Tools</h1>
</center>
<P>
<b>DCRS contact</b>: <a href="/DCRS/staff/jd.html">Jrgen Dall</a>, e-mail: <a href="mailto:jd@emi.dtu.dk">jd@emi.dtu.dk</a><br>
<p>
An important part of the technological program is the development
of efficient computer tools to process, evaluate, visualise, and
archive data from DCRS' own sensors but also from existing
and planned remote sensing satellites. This library of tools to
utilise data will include software to combine data acquired by
different sensors, to visualise data sets with many independent
channels, and to transform data between different map projections.
Processing and scientific analysis of the data collected by the
developed sensors will require significant expansions of computational
capabilities. The activities at DCRS includes studies on utilising
parallel computers. This activity will also support DCRS'
principal investigator (PI) studies on scientific applications
of data from the SAR on board the European Remote Sensing satellites,
ERS-1/-2.

<p>
<b>List of projects:</b><p>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="/DCRS/projects/emidans.html">Data Analysis System for ERS-1 Data</a>.<br>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="http://saturn.emi.dtu.dk/smp/">Parallel Processing</a>.<br>
<p>

<hr>
<address><a href="/DCRS/staff/bbt.html">Bjorn B. Thomsen &lt;bbt@emi.dtu.dk&gt;</a></address>
