  Direct Dial: +45 45 25 3791<BR>
  Telefax: +45 45 93 16 34<BR>
  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:ltp@emi.dtu.dk">ltp@emi.dtu.dk</A></P>

  <HR>

  <H2>Research</H2>
<p>
Primary field of research is <a href="/DCRS/seaIce.html">microwave remote sensing of sea ice </a>
  <H3>Educational Responsibilities</H3>
<p>
Courses in Digital image processing & Remote sensing
<p>
<h4>Present Special Courses:</h4>
<dl>
  <dt>MPEG coding of satellite image sequences
  <dt>Motion compensation of scanned video sequenses
</dl>
  <HR>

  <H2>Curriculum Vitae</H2>
<dl>

  <dt> Born 9 April 1957 in Hobro, Denmark
  <dt>M.Sc. in Electrical Engineering 1982 from the Technical University of Denmark (TUD). Thesis on passive microwave radiometry from the TUD microwave radiometer system. (Electromagnetics Institute).
  <dt>Ph.D. 1991 TUD. Thesis title: Retrieval of sea ice concentration by means of microwave radiometry.
  <dt>Has worked as a research scientist at the Electromagnetics Institute of the Technical University of Denmark from 1982 to present in connection with a number of remote sensing projects primarily related to sea ice.
</dl>
<h4>The projects include </h4>
<dl>
  <dt>East Greenland Current Project (development of geophysical methods) 1984-1986,
  <dt>MIZEX-83 & -87 (1983-1988),
  <dt>international Greenland Sea Project (GSP) 1987-1993,
  <dt>ESOP (European Subpolar Ocean Programme, EEC/MAST-II initiative) 1993-1996.
</dl>
Has been a principal investigator under the European utilization programme for the Japanese MOS-1 satellite (ESA). Has e
xperience with a large number of remote sensing data spanding the whole range from visual and infrared high-resolution data through medium-resolution data from NOAA-AVHRR to data from active and passive microwave instruments 
Has been a major designer of the integrated data analysis system developed at the Electromagnetics Institute.

