<html> <head>
<title>PELICON</title>
</head>

<body>
<center><h1><strong>PELICON</strong></h1></center>

 <center> <H1><IMG SRC="/images/ssmi-south.gif" border=4></H1></center>


<center><h1>Project for Estimation of Long-term variability in Ice CONcentration </h1></center>

<h3>Detailed description of the contribution of DCRS</h3>
<p>

The analysis of multispectral passive microwave observations in order to derive sea ice related parameters such as ice concentration and ice type requires both regional and seasonal calibration of the algorithms applied (Pedersen, 1991). The purpose of the proposed project is to establish methods for performing this calibration using visible and infrared images from NOAA, LANDSAT and SPOT satellites. In particular, the effect of variability in weather effects and surface conditions on PMI ice concentration estimates will be addressed.


