<html> <head>
<title>Sea ice scattering mechanisms </title>
</head>

<body>
<h1>Sea ice scattering mechanisms </h1>
<p>
This study concerns the possibilities of using
polarimetric SAR observations to enhance our knowledge about scattering
mechanisms at the ice surface and within the ice. Development
of models of active and passive microwave signatures of sea ice
is an important activity, essential to the process of combining
data from different airborne and satellite sensors with different
resolution and mapping geometry. DCRS is the PI on an ERS-1/-2
investigation on this subject.

<hr>
<address></address>
