 <HEAD><TITLE>Jrgen Dall at EMI</TITLE></HEAD>

 <BODY>

  <H1><IMG SRC="/images/jd.gif"> Jrgen Dall</H1>

  <STRONG> </STRONG>
  <P>
  Electromagnetics Institute<br>
  DTU, Building 348, room 124<br>
  DK-2800 Lyngby<br>

  <P>Telephone: +45 45 88 14 44, ext. 3842<BR>
  Direct Dial: +45 45 25 3842<BR>
  Telefax: +45 45 93 16 34<BR>
  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:jd@emi.dtu.dk">jd@emi.dtu.dk</A></P>

<p>
<b>J&oslash;rgen Dall,  M.Sc.E.E.'84, Ph.D.'89.</b>
<p>
He has been with the Electromagnetics Institute, Technical University of Denmark since 1984, when he conducted an ESA study of microwave instruments for planetary missions. Among the recent activities are the development of algorithms for polarimetric calibration of the Danish airborne SAR (EMISAR), and technical management of a SAR processing facility for semi-operational processing of EMISAR data. He was responsible for the development of a dedicated onboard full resolution real-time processor for EMISAR, and prior to that he implemented software processors for the SEASAT SAR and EMISAR systems. Other SAR activities have included development of a novel SAR autofocus algorithm, and studies of fast transform and convolution algorithms for SAR processing. He is now leading the SAR processing group at the Danish Center for Remote Sensing (DCRS).
<p>
