<html> <head>
<title>Data Analysis System for ERS-1 Data</title>
</head>

<body>
<center>
 <h1>Data Analysis System for ERS-1 Data</h1>
</center>

<P>
<B>DCRS contact</b>: <a href="/DCRS/staff/bbt.html">Bjorn B. Thomsen</a>, e-mail: <a href="mailto:bbt@emi.dtu.dk">bbt@emi.dtu.dk</A>
<P>

The objective of the project is to develop an integrated analysis system for
remote sensing data to be used on UNIX workstations. This
analysis system will be constructed of a list of modules, which takes care of
specific tasks in the system.
<p>
The tasks includes display of images, data visualization in windows, in
addition to image processing functions such as filtering, classification,
segmentation, and geometrical rectification. One module will contain a range
of algorithms to analyze data for specific purposes, such as sea ice,
oceanography, forestry, and agriculture.
<p>
The user will be able to without particular knowledge about the operations of
the sensor to extract information from the satellite data with the help of
advanced applications.
<p>
The project is funded by the <I>Danish Technical Research Council (STVF)</I>.
<P>
<B>Project related publications</B>:
<dl>
  <dt>R 599
  <dd> Niels J. Bagger<br>
       <I><a href="/proj/proj.html">Projection Functions</a></I><br>
       November 1994.
       <p>
  <dt>P ?
  <dd> Niels J. Bagger, Leif Toudal Pedersen, Henning Skriver, and Preben Gudmandsen,<br>
       <a href="/DCRS/abstracts/bagger95.html"><I>Data Analysis System for Remote Sensing Data</I></a><br>
       1st International Symposium about Scientific Imagery and Image Processing, Cannes 1995
</dl>
<P>
