 <HEAD><TITLE>Erik Lintz Christensen at EMI</TITLE></HEAD>

 <BODY>

  <H1><IMG SRC="/images/elc.gif"> Erik Lintz Christensen</H1>

  <STRONG> </STRONG>
  <P>
  Electromagnetics Institute<br>
  DTU, Building 348, room 114<br>
  DK-2800 Lyngby<br>

  <P>Telephone: +45 45 88 14 44, ext. 3835<BR>
  Direct Dial: +45 45 25 3835<BR>
  Telefax: +45 45 93 16 34<BR>
  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:elc@emi.dtu.dk">elc@emi.dtu.dk</A></P>
<p>
<b>Erik Lintz Christensen, M.Sc.E.E. '66</b>
<p>
In 1968 he joined the Electromagnetics 
Institute, Technical University of Denmark, where he is now an associate 
professor. His work has covered many aspects of radar, radio communications, 
and high frequency and microwave electronics. This includes the design of 60 
MHz and 300 MHz radars for recording of the thickness of the inland ice of 
Greenland and Antarctica, equipment for measuring amplitude and phase of the 
transfer function of a 50 km line-of-sight radio path at 15 GHz, a system for 
measuring amplitude and phase of antenna near-field patterns.
From 1990 to 1994
he was the project manager of the Danish Airborne SAR program now integrated 
into the Danish Center for Remote Sensing. Since February 1994 he is a 
co-manager of the Danish Center for Remote Sensing.
<p>

