<html> <head>
<title>Latest SSM/I derived ice concentrations from the Greenland Sea</title>
</head>

<body>
<h1><center>Latest esop ice  and weather information</center></h1>
<p>
<h2> Ice information </h2>

DCRS produces daily ice maps from the Greenland Sea region as well as from South- and West-Greenland
waters. The original SSM/I antenna temperature data are supplied by the The <a href="http://wwwdaac.msfc.nasa.gov/daac.html">NASA Earth Observing System, Hydrologic Cycle DAAC</A> at the Global Hydrology & Climate Center, Huntsville, Alabama.
<br>
<ul>
<li><a href="ftp://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/pub/ssmi/icemaps/latest/"> <b>All of today's images</b>  (SSM/I based ice maps) </a> produced by DCRS
<br>
<li><a href="ftp://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/pub/ssmi/icemaps/yesterday/"> <b>And yesterday's </b></a>images are available as well!
<br>
<li>     <a href="/images/aniser96.mpg">Animation of >180 days in feb-sep 96 </a>  -- updated 10/9  ( >850 KByte ) produced by DCRS
<li>Previous images can be found in the <a href="ftp://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/pub/noaa/1996/.directory.html"> <b><large>DCRS Archive </large></b> </a>
     
</ul>
Through the Archive you can also get access to our new JAVA image browser that allows you to
zoom into the images, draw related vector information (coastlines and ice concentration contours
of the image and images from previous days).

<h3> Other sources of ice information </h3>
<ul>
<li><A HREF="http://polar.wwb.noaa.gov/seaice/Analyses.html"> NCEP Sea Ice Analysis Page</A>. (National Center for Environmental Prediction) Northern and southern hemisphere ice maps.
<li>             <DT><A HREF="ftp://130.133.7.203/pub/SEA-ICE/icetext.html">University of Berlin monthly ice info </A> in historical perspective

</ul>
     
<h3> Other sources of weather information (university of Cologne and Karlsruhe)</h3>
<ul>
<li>        <DT><A HREF="http://www.uni-koeln.de/math-nat-fak/geomet/meteo/winfos/front00_00.gif">Analysis North Atlantic region, - today</A> (Kln)
<li>           <DT><A HREF="http://www.uni-koeln.de/math-nat-fak/geomet/meteo/winfos/front24_00.gif" >24 hour forecast North Atlantic region</A> (Kln)
<li>          <DT><A HREF="http://www.uni-koeln.de/math-nat-fak/geomet/meteo/winfos/front48_72.gif">48 and 72 hour forecast North Atlantic region</A> (Kln)
<li>           <DT><A HREF="http://www.uni-koeln.de/math-nat-fak/geomet/meteo/winfos/TTeuropa.gif"> Latest surface observations, North Atlantic region</A> (Kln)
<li>           <DT><A HREF="http://www.uni-koeln.de/math-nat-fak/geomet/meteo/winfos/arcisoTTPPWW.gif"> Surface temperatures and sea level pressure, North Atlantic region</A> (Kln)
<li>           <DT><A HREF="http://www.uni-koeln.de/math-nat-fak/geomet/meteo/winfos/synNNWWarctis.gif">Latest surface observations, Arctic region</A> (Kln)

<li>           <DT><A HREF="http://www.uni-karlsruhe.de/~bh28/pics/Rislsyn.gif">Station map, Iceland, South Greenland and Jan Mayen </A> (Karlsruhe)
<li>           <DT><A HREF="http://www.uni-karlsruhe.de/~bh28/pics/Rtavn002.gif">850 hPa Geopot. and Temperatures, North Atlantic</A> (Karlsruhe)

</ul>

