<html> <head>
<title>Data Analysis System for Remote Sensing Data, abstract</title>
</head>

<body>
<b>Title</b>: Data Analysis System for Remote Sensing Data (abstract)<p>
<b>Authors</b>: Niels J. Bagger, Leif Toudal Pedersen, Henning Skriver, and Preben Gudmandsen<p>
<b>Place</b>: 1st International Symposium about Scientific Imagery and Image Processing, Cannes 1995<p>

  In July 1991 ESA launched the European remote sensing satellite
  ERS-1 which still delivers a large amount of data from its sensors. At
  Electromagnetics Institute (EMI) at the Technical University of Denmark, we
  have used this data along with data from other sources for our scientific
  research of eg.\ sea ice for many years. As a result of these studies, a lot
  of algorithms have been developed to extract information about ice
  concentration, classification, and ice movements.
<p>
  To simplify the analysis process, we are at EMI currently working on a
  project to develop an integrated analysis system, which will enable the user
  to extract information especially from satellite data together with other
  remote sensing data and data from other sources. The user will be able to
  without particular knowledge about the operations of the sensor to extract
  information from the satellite data with the help of advanced applications.
<p>
  The system is constructed of modules, each which handles specific
  tasks. Among the modules are the <i>display module</i> for viewing images,
  the <i>process module</i> for the collection of algorithms eg. filtering,
  segmentation and geometric rectification, and the <i>database module</i>
  for storing and searching for data.
<p>
  Today a prototype of the display module has been developed for the X Window
  System. The display system is especially developed to display images
  containing our own image header. This header contains together with other
  data, information about the projection, which the image has been fitted to,
  enabling the display system to show a wide range of geographical related
  data with the image.

<p>
<hr>
<address><a href="/DCRS/staff/bbt.html">Bjorn B. Thomsen</a> <a href="mailto:bbt@emi.dtu.dk">&lt;bbt@emi.dtu.dk&gt;</a></address>
<!-- hhmts start -->
