<html> <head>
<title>Addendum to "EMI Image Header and I/O System version 3" report</title>
</head>

<body>
<h1>Addendum to "EMI Image Header and I/O System version 3" report</h1>

This page contains items that has been changed or added to the
<a href="http:/manuals/emiio/emiheader.html">EMI Image Header and I/O System version
3</a> draft report of February 1995.
<p>
Please let <a href="mailto:bbt@emi.dtu.dk">me</a> know, if you find items that
should be changed or added to the report before the final copy
<p>
<hr>
<ol>
  <li> <b>Added a constructor to the <tt>Buffer</tt> template class.</b> (p. 98)<br>
       Two new constructors has been added to the class, which takes a
       <tt>IDim<uint32></tt> dimension value as the first argument.<br>
       <p>
       <dl>
	 <dt> <tt>Buffer(uintDim </tt><i>dim</i><tt>, T*</tt> <i>abuf</i><tt>=NULL);</tt>
	 <dd> The constructor initializes an instance of the class with a
	      buffer of the given dimension <i>dim</i>.
	      <p>
	      If <i>abuf</i> is non-NULL, the buffer data will point to this
	      array. The given array <i>must</i> be large enough to hold
	      <i>dim.l</i> x <i>sim.s</i> x <i>type-size</i> number of bytes,
	      where <i>type-size</i> is the size in bytes of one data element
	      (<tt>T<tt>).
	      <p>
	      If <i>abuf</i> is NULL, a buffer data area will be allocated by
	      the constructor.
	      <p>
	      The internal position pointer will be set to (l,s) = (0,0).
	      <p>
       <dt> <tt>Buffer(uintDim </tt><i>dim</i><tt>, T </tt><i>i_val</i>);
	    <dd> The constructor initializes an instance of the class by
		 allocating a buffer with the given dimensions.
		 <p>
		 The buffer is initialized with <i>i\_val</i> at each position.
		 <p>
		 The internal position pointer will be set to (l,s) = (0,0).
		 <p>
       </dl>
  <li> <b>Corrected the spelling error for the <tt>IDim</tt> type definition.</b> (p. 104)<br>
       The second line of the type definitions should read:
       <p>
         <tt>typedef uintDim IDim&lt;uint32&gt;</tt> Unsigned 32-bit integer
       <p>
       
</ol>
<hr>
<address><a href="/DCRS/staff/bbt.html">Bjorn B. Thomsen&lt;bbt@emi.dtu.dk&gt;</a></address>
