<H1><A NAME=SECTION00330000000000000000> Ice types observed from satellite microwave sensors</A></H1>
<P>
In this section, the signature from active and passive microwave sensors of various
types of sea ice will be explained.
The sensors of primary interest are the passive microwave radiometer on board the 
Special Sensor Microwave/Imager (<A HREF="http://wwwdaac.msfc.nasa.gov:5721/sensor_documents/ssmi_sensor.html">SSM/I</A>) and the Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) on 
board the <A HREF="http://gds.esrin.esa.it:80/A1F01400/CERS1.1">ERS-1</A> satellite.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<UL> 
<LI> <A NAME=tex2html219 HREF="node7.html#SECTION00331000000000000000"> Passive microwave radiometer</A>
