<meta name="description" value=" Open Water">
<meta name="keywords" value="odden-ice-report">
<meta name="resource-type" value="document">
<meta name="distribution" value="global">
</HEAD>
<BODY><P>
 <BR> <HR><A NAME=tex2html261 HREF="node10.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html259 HREF="node8.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html253 HREF="node8.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html263 HREF="node1.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME=tex2html262 HREF="node10.html"> Grease ice</A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME=tex2html260 HREF="node8.html"> Synthetic aperture radar </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME=tex2html254 HREF="node8.html"> Synthetic aperture radar </A>
<BR> <HR> <P>
<H3><A NAME=SECTION00332100000000000000> Open Water</A></H3>
<P>
When wind is blowing, the open water areas appears bright in SAR images, 
whereas they are dark in calm weather.
An approximate of the backscatter as function of wind speed and angle of 
incidence can be found by using the CMOD-4 model <A HREF="node61.html#cmod4">[ESA, 1993]</A>.
This is shown in figure <A HREF="node9.html#figwater_backscatter"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="gif" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/cross_ref_motif.gif"></A>.
<P>
<P><A NAME=45>&#160;</A><A NAME=figwater_backscatter>&#160;</A><A HREF="_43430_figure33-large.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_43430_figure33.gif"></A>
<BR><STRONG>Figure:</STRONG> Backscatter from open water as function of wind speed and angle of incidence<BR>
<P>
<P>
They are often homogeneous without any texture of significance. 
In the presence of ocean currents or local wind differences in an area, 
patterns can be formed in the image. 
An example of wind blown open water is shown in figure <A HREF="node9.html#figwater"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="gif" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/cross_ref_motif.gif"></A>.
<P><A NAME=52>&#160;</A><A NAME=figwater>&#160;</A><A HREF="_43430_figure49-large.jpg"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_43430_figure49.gif"></A>
<BR><STRONG>Figure:</STRONG> Open water on January 15 1993<BR>
<P>
<P>
<BR> <HR>
