<BR> <HR> <P>
<H3><A NAME=SECTION00332200000000000000> Grease ice</A></H3>
<P>
Grease ice forms on the lee side of features if water and air temperatures are below
freezing. 
It appears dark in SAR images, and it has a texture known as wavy.
In the presence of ocean currents or local winds, grease ice is expected to form patterns 
similar to those of open water.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<a href="/DCRS/staff/tff.html">Tim Flintholm Fink</a><A HREF="mailto:tff@emi.dtu.dk">&lt;tff@emi.dtu.dk&gt;</A><BR><I>
