<H3><A NAME=SECTION00332600000000000000> Convection created patterns in ocean</A></H3>
<P>
Convection makes the ocean form local currents, indicated by eddies and plumes.
When the ocean is covered with grease ice or pancake ice,
these patterns can sometimes be seen in SAR images.
An example of convection created ocean currents is shown in figure <A HREF="node14.html#figpattern"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="gif" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/cross_ref_motif.gif"></A>.
<P><A NAME=75>&#160;</A><A NAME=figpattern>&#160;</A><A HREF="_43430_figure72-large.jpg"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_43430_figure72.gif"></A>
<BR><STRONG>Figure:</STRONG> Convection induced pattern on February 6 1993<BR>
<P>
<P>
