<B>Up:</B> <A NAME=tex2html405 HREF="node17.html"> Ice in the </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME=tex2html399 HREF="node18.html"> January 2 1993</A>
<BR> <HR> <P>
<H3><A NAME=SECTION00400200000000000000> January 8 1993</A></H3>
<P>
Most of the SAR image is covered with bright areas, and only thin dark bands
are present between the bright parts.
The bright parts are wind blown open water, while the dark bands are collections
of pancake ice. 
This can also be confirmed in the SSM/I image, where all parts are
covered with a low ice concentration.
The pancake ice bands appear homogeneous in the SAR image, which indicates, that
they are caused by a big number of small ice floes; smaller than the spatial resolution.
<P>
