<HEAD>
<TITLE> January 15 1993</TITLE>
<meta name="description" value=" January 15 1993">
<meta name="keywords" value="odden-ice-report">
<meta name="resource-type" value="document">
<meta name="distribution" value="global">
</HEAD>
<BODY><P>
 <BR> <HR><A NAME=tex2html428 HREF="node22.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html426 HREF="node17.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html420 HREF="node20.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html430 HREF="node1.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME=tex2html429 HREF="node22.html"> January 18 1993</A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME=tex2html427 HREF="node17.html"> Ice in the </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME=tex2html421 HREF="node20.html"> January 11 1993</A>
<BR> <HR> <P>
<H3><A NAME=SECTION00400400000000000000> January 15 1993</A></H3>
<P>
The SAR image has a dark feature in the image center and a bright appearance elsewhere.
The bright areas are wind blown open water, whereas the dark area is young smooth ice
or a dense concentration of pancake ice.
By comparing the SSM/I images from January 14 and January 15, it is seen, that the ice
is created during the 15'th.
The wind at the island Jan Mayen on January 15 is 8m/s <A HREF="node61.html#NMI">[NMI, 1993]</A>, which indicates,
that formation of pancake ice is likely.
In the SAR image, the ice has almost no texture except for a bright line along the 
northern ice edge, and a few very dark features in the ice.
At the ice edge some bands of new ice are seen, and the whole ice area is expected
to consist of pancake ice with slightly varying ice concentrations.
<P>
<BR><HR><a HREF="sar-images/930115.jpg"><tt>SAR.930115.jpg</tt></a><BR>
<BR><a HREF="ssmi-images/930115.gif"><tt>SSMI.930115.gif</tt></a><BR>
