<H3><A NAME=SECTION00400600000000000000> January 21 1993</A></H3>
<P>
In the SAR image, the upper bright part is easyly recognized as open water. 
Also in the lower right corner, open water is present.
In the central part, a dark background with some bright spots is seen.
The dark background is probably a high concentration of pancake ice, while the bright 
spots are open water between the ice.
A few very dark features are seen in the left hand side, which are recognized as
being new ice.
By comparison with the SSM/I image, good agreement is found.
<P>
