<H3><A NAME=SECTION004001100000000000000> January 28 1993</A></H3>
<P>
The SAR image shows, that open water is present in the upper left corner and in the
lower right corner.
In all of the central image, a grey background with some dark features are present.
The grey background can be formed by a mixture of pancake ice and open water.
The dark features are probably new ice or grease ice formed in calm conditions.
On January 27 the wind speed at Jan Mayen <A HREF="node61.html#NMI">[NMI, 1993]</A> is 5m/s, and at a weak wind like
this, new smooth ice can be formed.
<P>
