<H3><A NAME=SECTION004001500000000000000> February 3 1993</A></H3>
<P>
The SAR image is seen to be dominated by open water.
In the top part of the image, pancake ice with only a few open water regions are present.
In all the central part, open water and bands of pancake ice is dominating.
In the lower left corner, a bigger area of ice is seen.
This area is also assumed to be formed by pancake ice.
All of this is in good agreement with the SSM/I image (the upper 3 frames).
<P>
