<HEAD>
<TITLE> February 16 1993 (1)</TITLE>
<meta name="description" value=" February 16 1993 (1)">
<meta name="keywords" value="odden-ice-report">
<meta name="resource-type" value="document">
<meta name="distribution" value="global">
</HEAD>
<BODY><P>
 <BR> <HR><A NAME=tex2html692 HREF="node46.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html690 HREF="node17.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html684 HREF="node44.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html694 HREF="node1.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME=tex2html693 HREF="node46.html"> February 16 1993 </A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME=tex2html691 HREF="node17.html"> Ice in the </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME=tex2html685 HREF="node44.html"> February 15 1993</A>
<BR> <HR> <P>
<H3><A NAME=SECTION004002800000000000000> February 16 1993 (1)</A></H3>
<P>
In the upper 3 SAR frames, open water is clearly present in the upper left hand side.
Also in the lower left corner is open water seen.
This is in good agreement with the SSM/I image.
Along the ice edge long bands of very dark new ice are formed.
In the central part and right hand side of the image the ice concentration is quite high.
There is a dark background of almost consolidated pancake ice, and only with a 
few brighter areas with a significant water content.
There are also some very dark features of new ice.
<P>
<BR><HR><a HREF="sar-images/930216.1.jpg"><tt>SAR.930216.jpg</tt></a><BR>
<BR><a HREF="ssmi-images/930216.gif"><tt>SSMI.930216.gif</tt></a><BR>
<BR> <HR>
