<html> <head>
<title>Sea Ice</title>
</head>

<body>
<center><a  href="/images/IMG107.JPG"><IMG SRC="/images/berg.gif"></a></center>

<center><h1>Sea Ice </h1></center>
<P>
<p>
<b>DCRS contact</b>: <a href="/DCRS/staff/ltp.html">Leif Toudal</a>, e-mail: <a href="mailto:ltp@emi.dtu.dk">ltp@emi.dtu.dk</a><br>
<p>
Sea ice affects the climate as sea ice extent and type are important
parameters in determining the transport of heat and humidity from
the ocean to the atmosphere. Data from active and passive microwave
sensors contain information about sea ice that is not available
from other sources. In order to make better use of microwave remote
sensing techniques for monitoring sea ice conditions, it is necessary
to have detailed information about microwave signatures of major
types of sea ice.


<center><h2>Sea Ice observations</h2></center>
<P>
DCRS takes part in a number of national and International projects where remote sensing
in general and microwave remote sensing in particular is used as a tool for monitoring
sea ice.
<P>

<b>Projects include:</b> 
<P>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="esop.html">European Subpolar Ocean Project (esop) under MAST-II</a>
<P>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="pelicon.html"> Project for Estimation of Long-term variability in Ice CONcentration  (PELICON)</a>
<P>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="new.html"> Nort East Water polynya project (NEW)</a><P>

  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-g.gif"> <a href="wgrl-ice.html"> Microwave ice signatures in South/West Greenland waters  </a>
<P>

<center><h2>Sea Ice signatures</h2></center>

<P>

<b>Projects include:</b> 
<P>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-r.gif">  <a href="pmrice.html">Passive microwave signatures of sea ice</a>
<P>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-r.gif">  <a href="SAR-ice.html">Active microwave signatures of sea ice</a>
<P>
  <IMG SRC="/images/bullet-r.gif">  <a href="ice-scat.html">Sea ice scattering mechanisms</a>
<P>




<hr>
<address><a href="staff/ltp.html">Leif Toudal &lt;ltp@emi.dtu.dk&gt;</a></address>
