<H2><A NAME=SECTION00031000000000000000> Algorithms</A></H2>
<P>
<A NAME=sectionalgorithms>&#160;</A>
In this section, the 5 used algorithms to retrieve ice concentration will be 
outlined.<BR>Most algorithms are based on two simple equations:
<P><A NAME=equationunity>&#160;</A><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_equation25.gif"><P>
where <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap826.gif">, <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap824.gif"> and <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap874.gif"> are the amount of open water, multi-year ice and 
first-year ice, respectively.
<IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap824.gif"> is not to be confused with <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap822.gif"> from <A HREF="node2.html#equationF">equation 1</A>. The second formula is:
<P><A NAME=equationbrightness>&#160;</A><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_equation37.gif"><P>
where <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap886.gif"> is the brightness temperature and <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap888.gif">, 
<IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap840.gif"> and <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap842.gif"> are the brightness temperatures from open water, multi-year 
ice and first-year ice, respectively.<BR>The algorithms will be addressed separately below.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<UL> 
<LI> <A NAME=tex2html107 HREF="node5.html#SECTION00031100000000000000"> AES algorithm</A>
<LI> <A NAME=tex2html108 HREF="node6.html#SECTION00031200000000000000"> NORSEX algorithm</A>
<LI> <A NAME=tex2html109 HREF="node7.html#SECTION00031300000000000000"> Comiso (polarization) algorithm</A>
<LI> <A NAME=tex2html110 HREF="node8.html#SECTION00031400000000000000"> Comiso (frequency) algorithm</A>
<LI> <A NAME=tex2html111 HREF="node9.html#SECTION00031500000000000000"> NASA algorithm</A>
</UL>
