<BODY><P>
 <BR> <HR><A NAME=tex2html120 HREF="node6.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html118 HREF="node4.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html112 HREF="node4.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html122 HREF="node1.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME=tex2html121 HREF="node6.html"> NORSEX algorithm</A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME=tex2html119 HREF="node4.html"> Algorithms</A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME=tex2html113 HREF="node4.html"> Algorithms</A>
<BR> <HR> <P>
<H3><A NAME=SECTION00031100000000000000> AES algorithm</A></H3>
<P>
This is a two channel algorithm proposed by <A HREF="node17.html#swift">[Swift et al., 1985]</A>.
The algorithm models the atmosphere through a linear transformation from satellite 
measured antenna temperatures to ground estimated emissivities:
<P><A NAME=equationAES>&#160;</A><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_equation48.gif"><P>
where <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap844.gif"> is the emissivity, <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap858.gif"> is the antenna temperature, <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap848.gif"> is the 
temperature from free space, <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap850.gif"> is the average atmosphere temperature, <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap868.gif"> is 
the total atmospheric opacity and <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_35212_tex2html_wrap854.gif"> is the temperature at the surface.
<P>
In order to make the algorithm work properly, the satellite measured tie-points 
(brightness temperatures) have to be transformed to ground emissivities, using
this linear transformation.
The algorithm uses the channels 37V and 19H.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<a href="/DCRS/staff/tff.html">Tim Flintholm Fink</a><A HREF="mailto:tff@emi.dtu.dk">&lt;tff@emi.dtu.dk&gt;</A><BR><I>
Thu Oct 26 09:07:34 NFT 1995</I>
