<BR> <HR> <P>
<H1><A NAME=SECTION00200000000000000000> Introduction</A></H1>
<P>
 This is a reference manual of the projection functions available in
 C and FORTRAN. Some functions are additions to the EMI Image Header
 System <A HREF="node15.html#EMI">[1]</A> and cannot be used alone.
<P>
 These functions makes more than 70 map projections available through a 
 minimum set of interface functions. With these functions it is possible
 to make transformations between geographical, map, and image coordinates.
<P>
 To gain more information about the projections, please refer to the two
 projection reports produced by the United States Department of the Interior
 Geological Survey <A HREF="node15.html#usgs">[2]</A> and <A HREF="node15.html#proj4">[3]</A>. The reports are available on
 the USGS anonymous ftp-server:
 <tt>charon.er.usgs.gov</tt> (IP-address 128.128.40.24).
<P>
 <H2><A NAME=SECTION00201000000000000000> Overview</A></H2>
<P>
 The functions presented in this report has been build on the Cartographic
 Projection Procedures by Gerald I. Evenden at the United States Department
 of the Interior, Geological survey (USGS), <A HREF="node15.html#usgs">[2]</A> and <A HREF="node15.html#proj4">[3]</A>. The
 presented functions can be categorized in three groups:
<P>
 <OL>  <LI> Basic projection routines: <em>init_proj()</em>, and <em>proj()</em>.
  <LI> Geometric functions included in the EMI Image Header System <A HREF="node15.html#EMI">[1]</A>:
        <em>init_geom()</em>, <em>map()</em>, and <em>world()</em>.
  <LI> Information functions: <em>nprojparm()</em>, <em>projfix()</em>, 
        <em>projlbl()</em>, and <em>projparmlbl()</em>
 </OL>
<P>
 The functions in group 1 are used in applications not including the EMI
 Image Header System. Here the projection is initialized with a call to
 <em>init_proj()</em>, and the cartesian and geographical coordinates are
 calculated by calls to <em>proj()</em>.
<P>
 The functions in group 2 are used in applications that uses the EMI Image
 Header System. Here the projection is initialized with a call to
 <em>init_geom()</em>, and the image and geographical coordinates are calculated
 by calls to <em>map()</em> and <em>world()</em> respectively.
<P>
 The information functions in group 3 are used to retrieve textual information
 about the projections and their parameters. These functions can be used in
 conjunction with the group 1 functions as well as the group 2 functions.
<P>
 Chapter <A HREF="node3.html#chapfunc"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="gif" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/cross_ref_motif.gif"></A> contains references to the functions, and
 Appendix <A HREF="node13.html#appproj"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="gif" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/cross_ref_motif.gif"></A> contains lists of the available projections and their
 parameters. In Appendix <A HREF="node14.html#appellps"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="gif" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/cross_ref_motif.gif"></A> a list of available ellipse names is
 given.
<P>
 <H2><A NAME=SECTION00202000000000000000> Usage</A></H2>
<P>
 When the functions are used in C, some include files are necessary, since
 they define some constants needed in addition to offer prototypes for
 the functions. There exists two include files:
<P>
 <P><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tabular35.gif"><P>
<P>
 The four information functions look up in the database file <tt>.projections</tt>
 which contains all available projections. This file should be placed in the
 same directory as the EMI libraries, and a environment variable, 
 <tt>$EMIDBDIR</tt> <em>must</em> be set to this directory, e.g.:
<P>
 <tt>export EMIDBDIR=/usr/local/lib/emilib
<P>
 </tt>
<P>
 In order to use the referenced functions, four libraries has to be linked
 with the executable program:
<P>
 <P><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tabular54.gif"><P>
<P>
 This is done by specifying the follow arguments to the linker:
<P>
   ... <tt>-lproj -lemi -lm</tt>
 ...Make sure the linker knows where to find the libraries (the <tt>-L</tt> option).
<P>
 If the executable is to be used with the EMI Image Header System, additional
 libraries are needed. Please refer to <A HREF="node15.html#EMI">[1]</A> for more information.
<P>
 <BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I> Niels J. Bagger <BR>
Mon Jan 16 15:44:42 NFT 1995</I>
