<BR> <HR> <P>
<H1><A NAME=SECTION00330000000000000000> map</A></H1>
<P>
   map - Calculates the map coordinates for the worldly coordinates.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00332000000000000000> Synopsis</A></H2>
<P>
 C:
<pre>
<a href="node6.html#SECTION00334000000000000002">XY</A> map( imgID, latlon, irc )
   PID     imgID;
   <a href="node6.html#SECTION00334000000000000001">LatLon</a>  latlon;
   int *   irc;
</pre>
Inputs
<pre>
     imgID  Partition identifier
     latlon World coordinates latitude/longitude.
     irc    Function return code.
</pre>
<P>
 FORTRAN:
<pre>
SUBROUTINE MAP( IMGID, LAT, LON, L, S, IRC )
   INTEGER*4  IMGID
   REAL*8     LAT, LON
   REAL*8     L, S      (Return values)
   INTEGER*4  IRC       (Return value)
</pre>
Inputs
<pre>
     IMGID    Partition identifier.
     LAT, LON World coordinates latitude/longitude.
     L, S     The returned map coordinates.
     IRC      The function return code.
</pre>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00333000000000000000> Description</A></H2>
<P>
 <tt>map</tt> transforms the (latitude, longitude) coordinates into (line, sample)
 coordinates of the identified image. The initialization function, 
 <tt>init_geometric</tt> must be called once prior to this function.
<P>
 Be aware, if <tt>init_geometry</tt> was called with <tt>skip</tt> and/or
 <tt>mag</tt> parameters different from 1 (one), then the returned map coordinates
 are references to the <em>scaled</em> image's line/sample and <em>not</em> to
 the original image's.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00334000000000000000> Structures</A></H2>
<P>
<pre>
<A NAME=SECTION00334000000000000001>/* World coordinates structure */</A>
typedef struct {
   double  lat;  /* Latitude coordinate */
   double  lon;  /* Longitude coordinate */
} LatLon;
</pre>
<P>
<pre>
<A NAME=SECTION00334000000000000002>/* Map (rectangular) coordinates structure */</A>
typedef struct {
   double  x;  /* Sample (x) coordinate */
   double  y;  /* Line (y) coordinate */
} XY;
</pre>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00335000000000000000> Return value</A></H2>
<P>
 Possible error return codes:
<P>
<TABLE>
<TD ALIGN=left><b>1971</b><TD ALIGN=left>Partition specified not in use<TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00336000000000000000> Example</A></H2>
<P>
 C:
<pre>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <geom.h>


int     pid = 1;
int     irc = 0;
Rect    skip = { 1, 1 }
Rect    mag = { 1, 1 }
LatLon  latlon;
XY      xy;
:
:
getcom_( ... );
:
:
oldim_( ..., &pid, &irc );
:
:
if( !init_geometric(pid, skip, mag) ) {
  puts( "init_geometric failed!" );
  exit( 1 );
}
latlon.lat = 75.0;
latlon.lon = -20.0;
xy = map( pid, latlon, &irc );
if( irc!=0 )
  puts( "map problems!" );
</pre><P>
 FORTRAN:
<pre>
      INTEGER*4 IMGID
      REAL*8 LAT, LON
      REAL*8 X, Y
      INTEGER*4 IRC
      INTEGER*4 ONE


      ONE = 1


      OLDIM( ..., IMGID, IRC )
      :
      :
      CALL INIT_GEOMETRIC( IMGID, ONE, ONE, ONE, ONE, IRC )
      IF IRC.NE.0 GOTO 990
      CALL MAP( IMGID, LAT, LON, X, Y, IRC )
      :
      :
990   CONTINUE
      RETURN
</pre><P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00337000000000000000> See Also</A></H2>
<P>
 <a href="node4.html#SECTION00310000000000000000"><em>init_geometric()</em></a>, <a href="node11.html#SECTION00380000000000000000"><em>proj()</em></a>, <a href="node12.html#SECTION00390000000000000000"><em>world()</em></a>
<P>
