<H1><A NAME=SECTION00340000000000000000> nprojparm</A></H1>
<P>
   nprojparm - Returns the number of parameters for the projection.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00342000000000000000> Synopsis</A></H2>
<P>
 C:
<pre>
int nprojparm( pid )
   int  pid;
</pre>
Inputs
<pre>
     pid The projection ID.
</pre>
<P>
 FORTRAN:
<pre>
INTEGER*4 FUNCTION NPROJPARM( PID )
   INTEGER*4  PID
</pre>
Inputs
<pre>
     PID  The projection ID.
</pre>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00343000000000000000> Description</A></H2>
<P>
 The <tt>nprojparm()</tt> function returns the number of parameters needed
 to specify the given projection, <tt>pid</tt>.
<P>
 The information is found in the <tt>.projections</tt> database file found in
 the <tt>$EMIDBDIR</tt> directory.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00344000000000000000> Return value</A></H2>
<P>
 On success, the function returns the number of parameters, otherwise 0.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00345000000000000000> See Also</A></H2>
<P>
 <a href="node5.html#SECTION00320000000000000000"><em>init_proj()</em></a>
<P>
<BR> <HR>
