<H1><A NAME=SECTION00350000000000000000> projfix</A></H1>
<P>
   projfix - Returns the cartesian position of the fixpoint
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00352000000000000000> Synopsis</A></H2>
<P>
 C:
<pre>
char projfix( pid )
   int  pid;
</pre>
Inputs
<pre>
     pid The projection ID.
</pre>
<P>
 FORTRAN:
<pre>
CHARACTER FUNCTION PROJFIX( PID )
   INTEGER*4  PID
</pre>
Inputs
<pre>
     PID  The projection ID.
</pre>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00353000000000000000> Description</A></H2>
<P>
 The <tt>projfix()</tt> function returns the position of the fixpoint, as either
 the upper-left corner '<tt>U</tt>', or the center '<tt>C</tt>'.
<P>
 The information is found in the <tt>.projections</tt> database file found in
 the <tt>$EMIDBDIR</tt> directory.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00354000000000000000> Return value</A></H2>
<P>
 On success, the function returns '<tt>U</tt>' for the upper-left corner, or
 '<tt>C</tt>' for the center, otherwise 0.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00355000000000000000> See Also</A></H2>
<P>
 <a href="node4.html#SECTION00310000000000000000"><em>init_geom()</em></a>
<P>
<BR> <HR>
