<BR> <HR> <P>
<H1><A NAME=SECTION00380000000000000000> proj</A></H1>
<P>
   proj - The projection function.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00382000000000000000> Synopsis</A></H2>
<P>
 C:
<pre>
<a href="node11.html#SECTION00384000000000000001">UV</a> proj( ref, inv, data )
   void *  ref;
   int     inv;
   UV      data;
</pre>
Inputs
<pre>
     ref  Reference to the initialized structure (init_proj).
     inv  Conversion direction: 0: (lat,lon)-&gt;(x,y); 1: (x,y)-&gt;(lat,lon).
     data The input coordinates.
</pre>
<P>
 FORTRAN:
<pre>
SUBROUTINE PROJ( REF, INV, INP1, INP2, OUTP1, OUTP2 )
   INTEGER*4  REF
   INTEGER*4  INV
   REAL*8     INP1, INP2
   REAL*8     OUTP1, OUTP2  (Return values)
</pre>
Inputs
<pre>
     REF           Reference to the initialized structure (init_proj).
     INV           Conversion direction: 0: (lat,lon)-&gt;(x,y); 1: (x,y)-&gt;(lat,lon).
     INP1, INP2    The input coordinates.
     OUTP1, OUTP2  The output coordinates.
</pre>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00383000000000000000> Description</A></H2>
<P>
 The <tt>proj</tt> function converts geographic latitude and longitude coordinates
 into cartesian coordinates, <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1528.gif">, or the
 inverse, <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1530.gif">.
<P>
 The <tt>INV</tt> parameter specifies the convert direction. If <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1538.gif">
 then <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1534.gif"> and <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1536.gif"> respectively for C and FORTRAN. If
 <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1538.gif"> then <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1540.gif"> and <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1542.gif">.
<P>
 In the C case the function return with the result of the conversion. In
 FORTRAN the <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1544.gif"> parameters contains the 
 result.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00384000000000000000> Structures</A></H2>
<P>
<pre>
<A NAME=SECTION00384000000000000001>/* Parameter passing structure */</A>
typedef struct {
   double  u;
   double  v;
} UV;
</pre><P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00385000000000000000> Return value</A></H2>
<P>
 On success, the function returns the converted values.
<P>
 On error, the converted values equals <tt>HUGE_VAL</tt> as defined in
 <tt>math.h</tt>.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00386000000000000000> Example</A></H2>
<P>
 C:
<pre>
#include <proj.h>
#include <stdio.h>


void    *ref
UV      data =   { 55.0,  /* Latitude */
                   20.0   /* Longitude */
                 }
UV      out;
double  parm[] = { 32, /* zone */
                   0.0 /* south */
                 }
ref = init_proj( 103, parm, NULL ); /* UTM Projection */
out = proj( ref, 0, data );  /* Forward conversion */
:
:
</pre>
<P>
 FORTRAN:
<pre>
      INTEGER*4 REF
      INTEGER*4 PID
      REAL*8 PARM(8)
      INTEGER*4 FLAG, ZERO
      REAL*8 INP1, INP2
      REAL*8 OUTP1, OUTP2
C
      ZERO = 0
      PID = 103
      PARM(1) = 32D0
      PARM(2) = 0D0
      FLAG = 0
C Initialize the UTM Projection
      CALL INIT_PROJ( REF, PID, PARM, ZERO, ZERO, ZERO, ZERO, ZERO,
     +   ZERO, ZERO, FLAG )
C
      INP1 = 55D0
      INP2 = 20D0
C Forward conversion
      PROJ( REF, ZERO, INP1, INP2, OUTP1, OUTP2 )
      :
      :
</pre>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00387000000000000000> See Also</A></H2>
<P>
 <a href="node5.html#SECTION00320000000000000000"><em>init_proj()</em></a>, <a href="node6.html#SECTION00330000000000000000"><em>map()</em></a>, <a href="node12.html#SECTION00390000000000000000"><em>world()</em></a>.
<P>
