<BODY><P>
 <BR> <HR><A NAME=tex2html238 HREF="node13.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html236 HREF="node3.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html232 HREF="node11.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html240 HREF="node1.html"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="/u/emilib/lib/perl/latex2html/icons/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME=tex2html239 HREF="node13.html"> Available projections</A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME=tex2html237 HREF="node3.html"> Functions</A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME=tex2html233 HREF="node11.html"> proj</A>
<BR> <HR> <P>
<H1><A NAME=SECTION00390000000000000000> world</A></H1>
<P>
   world - Calculates the world coordinates from map coordinates.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00392000000000000000> Synopsis</A></H2>
<P>
 C:
<pre>
<a href="node12.html#SECTION00394000000000000001">LatLon</a> world( imgID, xy, irc )
   PID    imgID;
   <a href="node12.html#SECTION00394000000000000002">XY</a>     xy;
   int *  irc;
</pre>
Inputs
<pre>
     imgID Partition identifier
     xy    Map coordinates line/sample.
     irc   Function return code.
</pre>
<P>
 FORTRAN:
<pre>
SUBROUTINE WORLD( IMGID, L, S, LAT, LON, IRC )
   INTEGER*4  IMGID
   REAL*8     L, S
   REAL*8     LAT, LON  (Return values)
   INTEGER*4  IRC       (Return value)
</pre>
Inputs
<pre>
     IMGID    Partition identifier.
     L, S     The map coordinates line/sample.
     LAT, LON The returned world coordinates.
     IRC      The function return code.
</pre>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00393000000000000000> Description</A></H2>
<P>
 <tt>world</tt> transforms the (line, sample) coordinates into (longitude, latitude)
 coordinates of the identified image. The initialization function, 
 <tt>init_geometric</tt> must be called once prior to this function.
<P>
 Be aware, if <tt>init_geometry</tt> was called with <tt>skip</tt> and/or
 <tt>mag</tt> parameters different from 1 (one), then the map coordinates
 are references to the <em>scaled</em> image's line/sample and <em>not</em> to
 the original image's.
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00394000000000000000> Structures</A></H2>
<P>
<pre>
<A NAME=SECTION00394000000000000001>/* World coordinates structure */</A>
typedef struct {
   double  lat;  /* Latitude coordinate */
   double  lon;  /* Longitude coordinate */
} LatLon;
</pre>
<P>
<pre>
<A NAME=SECTION00394000000000000002>/* Map (rectangular) coordinates structure */</A>
typedef struct {
   double  x;  /* Sample (x) coordinate */
   double  y;  /* Line (y) coordinate */
} XY;
</pre>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00395000000000000000> Return value</A></H2>
<P>
 Possible error return codes:
<P>
<TABLE>
<TD ALIGN=left><b>1971</b><TD ALIGN=left>Partition specified not in use<TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00396000000000000000> Example</A></H2>
<P>
 C:
<pre>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <geom.h>

int     pid = 1;
int     irc = 0;
Rect    skip = { 1, 1 }
Rect    mag = { 1, 1 }
LatLon  latlon;
XY      xy;
:
:
getcom_( ... );
:
:
oldim_( ..., &pid, &irc );
:
:
if( !init_geometric(pid, skip, mag) ) {
  puts( "init_geometric failed!" );
  exit( 1 );
}
xy.l = 100;
xy.s = 1;
latlon = world( pid, xy, &irc );
if( irc!=0 )
  puts( "world problems!" );
</pre>
<P>
 FORTRAN:
<pre>
      INTEGER*4 IMGID
      REAL*8 LAT, LON
      REAL*8 X, Y
      INTEGER*4 IRC
      INTEGER*4 ONE


      ONE = 1


      OLDIM( ..., IMGID, IRC )
      :
      :
      CALL INIT_GEOMETRIC( IMGID, ONE, ONE, ONE, ONE, IRC )
      IF IRC.NE.0 GOTO 990
      CALL WORLD( IMGID, X, Y, LAT, LON, IRC )
      :
      :
990   CONTINUE
      RETURN
</pre>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00397000000000000000> See Also</A></H2>
<P>
 <em>init_geometric()</em>, <em>proj()</em>, <em>map()</em>
<P>
