<H1><A NAME=SECTION00400000000000000000> Available projections</A></H1>
<P>
 <A NAME=appproj>&#160;</A>
<P>
  <H2><A NAME=SECTION00401000000000000000> Description</A></H2>
<P>
  The columns of the following pages describes the following:
<P>
  <DL >   <DT>No
<DD> is the projection identify number. Constants are defined in
      <tt>proj.h</tt>.
   <DT>Projection Name
<DD> is the name label of the projection.
   <DT>Type
<DD> is the projection type. Abbreviations used:
     <b>C</b>onformal, <b>I</b>nverse, <b>S</b>pherical, <b>E</b>lliptical,
     and Equal <b>A</b>rea.
   <DT>Fix
<DD> is the fixpoint used in the <tt>map()</tt> and <tt>world()</tt>.
     Labeled either <tt>U</tt> for upper-left corner or <tt>C</tt> for center.
   <DT>Parameters
<DD> are the list of parameters needed to initialize the
     projection. <em>They must be given in the specified order!</em> (See also
     <em>init_proj()</em> and <em>init_geom()</em>).
   <DT>Reference
<DD> tells where to read more about the projection and its
     parameters in the two included USGS reports.
<P>
 </DL>
<P>
 <H2><A NAME=SECTION00402000000000000000> Cylindrical Projections</A></H2>
<P>
 <P><A NAME=1476>&#160;</A><A NAME=tabcyl>&#160;</A><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_table541.gif">
<BR><STRONG>Table:</STRONG> Parameters needed for the cylindrical projections. Types: <b>C</b>onformal, <b>I</b>nverse, <b>S</b>pherical, <b>E</b>lliptical, and Equal <b>A</b>rea. <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1726.gif"> <tt>south</tt> is set with <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1728.gif">. Should be <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="_24619_tex2html_wrap1730.gif"> otherwise<BR>
<P>
<P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00403000000000000000> Pseudocylindrical Projections</A></H2>
<P>
