<html> <head>
<title>Latest SSM/I derived ice concentrations from South-West Greenland</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1><center>Latest South-west Greenland  ice information</center></h1>
<p>
<b> This is preliminary data, not geometrically checked. 
Should be used with great
care, and should NOT be used as primary source of ice information for this area !!</b>
<p>
<a href="ftp://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/pub/ssmi/icemaps/latest/"> All of today's images  </a> now available, <b> note </b>that these images may be more recent than the ones found on this page below. <p>
<a href="ftp://www.dcrs.dtu.dk/pub/ssmi/icemaps/yesterday/"> And yesterday's  </a> <p>

<center><a  href="/images/w9620222A.ssmice.gif"><IMG SRC="/images/w9620222A.ssmice.gif"" border=0></a></center>
<h3><center> July 20 1996    18:35 UTC</center></h3>
<p>

<h3><center>Most recent SSM/I derived ice concentrations </center></h3>
<p>

Colours are according to pseudo ice concentration derived by a special algorithm combining data at 19 and 37 GHz with the
spatial resolution of the 85 GHz channels.
They reveal details about the ice cover on an improved spatial resolution compared with the traditional low frequency
based algorithms.
<p>
The white curve is the coastline of Greenland.
<p>
Image is displayed and manipulated by the DCRS developed EMImage display
software.
<p>
