<h1>Welcome to NIRSNET on the Web</h1>

<p><a href="nirsweb.gif"><img src="nirsweb.gif" border=2 height=60 width=300></a></p>

<p>Welcome to NIRSNET on the Web! This area is now completely indexed.
We are trying to add new files daily, and we are updating the indexes as
frequently as possible. NIRS' Webboard is also active and working; see
below.</p>

<p>NIRS has completed transfer of the files previously on the NIRSNET bbs.
Below is a list of several file areas. Each file area is indexed separately.
Because of the huge volume of files now on this web, we are no longer listing
each document individually. Rather, we will list new and particularly interesting
documents in each file category. For more information, contact NIRS at
<a href="mailto:nirsnet@igc.apc.org">nirsnet@igc.apc.org</a> or call 202-328-0002.
Thanks. We hope NIRSNET on the Web meets your needs. You may also send
your suggestions for improvement and comments to the above e-mail address
directly from this site. </p>

<p>
<hr></p>

<h2><img src="new.gif" border=0 height=13 width=32 align=bottom><a href="http://www.nirs.org/webboard/$webb.exe">Check
out the new NIRS Webboard!</a></h2>

<p>Discuss issues and ideas with activists from around the world. Ask for
help, offer help. Dialogue with industry if you want, and vice-versa. Communicate.</p>

<p>You will be asked for a user name and a password. The username is used
solely to log into the NIRS Webboard and should not be your real name.
Make up a name and password that you'll remember easily. Once logged in
the first time, you will be asked to fill out a very brief questionnaire.
All messages within the NIRS Webboard will be signed with your real name.</p>

<p>
<hr></p>

<h1>File Areas</h1>

<ul>
<p><a href="reactor/reacbbs.htm">Nuclear reactors &amp; nuclear safety</a></p>

<p><a href="llw/llwbbs.htm">&quot;Low-level&quot; radioactive waste</a></p>

<p><a href="hlw/hlwbbs.htm">High-level radioactive waste</a></p>

<p><a href="radiation/radbbs.htm">Radiation</a></p>

<p><a href="fedreg/fdregbbs.htm">Federal Register notices</a></p>

<p><a href="grassroots/grasbbs.htm">Dispatches from the Grassroots;</a>
includes information from local safe energy &amp; environmental groups,
newsletters from Ozone Action, A Clear View, Free the Planet, and much
more (note: if your group would like to contribute to this area, please
send your newsletters, press releases, reports, studies, and other info
to nirsnet@igc.apc.org in ASCII or html format, unencoded).</p>

<p><a href="intl/intlgbbs.htm">International news and grassroots actions,</a>
activities and information. Send us your info, we will post it.</p>

<p><a href="dereg/decombbs.htm">Decommissioning and radiation deregulation</a></p>

<p><a href="economic/econbbs.htm">Nuclear economics and utility deregulation</a></p>

<p><a href="fuelcycle/cyclebbs.htm">Fuel cycle facilities and issues</a></p>

<p><a href="alternatives/altbbs.htm">Alternatives to nuclear power</a></p>

<p><a href="wir/wirbbs.htm">NRC Commissioners' Weekly Information Report</a></p>

<p><a href="dailyrpt/derbbs.htm">Daily Event Reports</a></p>
</ul>

<ul>
<p><a href="nrcadmin/nrcadbbs.htm">NRC and administrative files</a></p>

<p><a href="rehw/rehwbbs.htm">Rachel's Environment &amp; Health Weekly</a></p>

<p><a href="wew/aweabbs.htm">American Wind Energy Weekly</a></p>
</ul>

<p>NIRSNET on the Web is updated regularly. If you don't find what you're
looking for, check again soon. If you have a request for a special document
or area not listed above, send a message to <a href="mailto:nirsnet@igc.apc.org">nirsnet@igc.apc.org</a>
</p>

