<BODY LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#FF0000" ALINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="paper1.gif">

<P><IMG SRC="dwalog.gif" HEIGHT=158 WIDTH=200> </P>

<H1>Don't Waste America</H1>

<P>The nuclear power industry is pushing Congress to establish an &quot;interim&quot;
high-level radioactive waste storage dump near Yucca Mountain, Nevada.
This proposal, encapsulated in H.R. 1020 and S. 167, would set into motion
the unprecedented transportation of high-level nuclear waste through 43
states and hundreds of towns and cities--probably yours! This legislation
is unneeded and dangerous. Rather than try yet another doomed &quot;quick
fix,&quot; it would be far better to establish an Independent Commission
to fully re-examine and re-evaluate our nation's failed radioactive waste
policies. For more information, <A HREF="fctsht.htm">check out NIRS factsheets</A>.</P>

<P>SENATE VOTES 63-37 FOR S.1936, &quot;MOBILE CHERNOBYL ACT.&quot; <A HREF="1936up7.txt">ANALYSIS,
VOTE LIST,</A> August 1, 1996. Previous updates: <A HREF="1271last.htm">ALERT!
Act NOW! </A>Update <A HREF="1936up1.txt">#1 on S. 1936</A>, 7/12/96. <A HREF="1936up2.htm">Update
#2 on S. 1936</A>, 7/16/96, 3 pm. <A HREF="panetta.htm">Text of White House
letter, </A>7/15/96, reaffirming intent to veto S. 1936. Text of <A HREF="Lott1.htm">NIRS
letter to Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott</A>, calling for withdrawal
of S. 1936, July 17, 1996. <A HREF="Lottpr.htm">NIRS press release</A>,
July 17, 1997. <A HREF="1936up3.htm">Update #3 on S. 1936, </A>7/17/96,
3 pm. <A HREF="1936up4.htm">Update #4,</A> 7/23/96, 3:30 PM. Vote delayed
until Wednesday, July 31. <A HREF="1936up5.htm">Update #5,</A> 7/24/96.</P>

<P><IMG SRC="redline.gif" HEIGHT=2 WIDTH=640 ALIGN=CENTER> </P>

<P>View a map showing likely U.S. radioactive waste <A HREF="fulltran.gif">rail
transportation routes</A> with reactor names. Or view a map showing likely
<A HREF="fultran2.gif">highway transportation routes</A> with reactor names.
Or view a map showing <A HREF="fultran1.gif">both rail and highway routes</A>
(without reactor names). You can also <A HREF="maps.htm">view maps of each
state's</A> likely transport routes (note, these files are much smaller
than the above).</P>

<P><IMG SRC="new.gif" HEIGHT=13 WIDTH=32 ALIGN=BOTTOM><A HREF="mainmap.htm">Find
your state and Congressional District!</A> Radioactive waste transportation
volumes by congressional district and Congressmember. </P>

<P>You can help! Download, sign and distribute the national <A HREF="dwapet.htm">Don't
Waste America petition</A>.</P>

<P>Encourage your town, city, and/or county councils to pass a resolution
against these bills and unnecessary radioactive waste transportation. You
can find a <A HREF="sampres.htm">sample resolution</A> here, as well as
the texts of resolutions already passed by Denver, Philadelphia, Santa
Barbara, and a number of other jurisdictions.</P>

<P><IMG SRC="redline.gif" HEIGHT=2 WIDTH=640 ALIGN=CENTER> </P>

<P><IMG SRC="new.gif" HEIGHT=13 WIDTH=32>Congressional Record <A HREF="Congrd.htm">Highlights
of Senate floor debate</A> on S. 1936!</P>

<P>83 organizations sign letter to Dole protesting upcoming Senate vote
on S. 1271. <A HREF="dolelttr.htm">Text of letter</A> and <A HREF="doleprer.htm">press
release</A> April 16, 1996 </P>

<P><A HREF="11895.htm">Letter to Congress</A>, 11/8/95, signed by numerous
environmental and religious leaders, against HR 1020 and for an independent
commission to re-evaluate current radioactive waste policy</P>

<P><A HREF="polltext.htm">Results of a public opinion poll</A>, conducted
during December 1995, which showed that 70% of the U.S. public prefers
establishment of an independent commission; 26% prefers immediate transportation
of radioactive waste, as called for by HR 1020. Includes statement by SECC
director Scott Denman.</P>

<P><A HREF="pollquot.htm">Statement of Michael Mariotte</A>, director of
NIRS, upon release of public opinion poll, January 18, 1996.</P>

<P><A HREF="presstf.htm">NIRS statement</A> at press conference October
17, 1995, at National Press Club on high-level waste transportation</P>

<P><A HREF="mapqa.htm">Question and answer</A> sheet on high-level waste
transport prepared by NIRS for October 17, 1995 press conference.</P>

<P>Contact NIRS for postcards to Congress, brochures and other printed
materials to distribute. 202-328-0002; fax: 202-462-2183; e-mail: nirsnet@igc.apc.org</P>

