<HEAD>
<TITLE>NIRS' Military-Industrial-Utility Complex Project</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]"></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper1.gif">
<H2>The Military-Industrial-Utility Complex</H2>
<P>The U.S. Department of Energy is preparing to approve the use of
plutonium-based (or MOX--mixed oxide) fuel in commercial nuclear reactors. In
addition, the DOE is preparing to encourage the production of tritium for
nuclear weapons in civilian reactors. These far-reaching steps violate every
non-proliferation principle advanced by the U.S. government for decades.</P>
<P>NIRS is unalterably opposed to the use of MOX fuel and the production of
tritium in commercial reactors. Use of MOX would contribute to the worldwide &quot;plutonium
economy,&quot; and would undercut our non-proliferation efforts worldwide. In
addition, it would produce more plutonium in so-called &quot;low-level&quot;
radioactive waste, exacerbate utility decommissioning efforts and increase
costs, expose more people to danger from plutonium through frequent shipments
across railways and highways, and would increase electricity costs.</P>
<P>Similarly, production of tritium in commercial reactors is little more than
a scheme to allow uneconomic reactors to operate with increased government
subsidies. Further, it would break down any remaining barrier between commercial
and military uses of nuclear energy--leaving us with a new, and frighteningly
powerful military-industrial-utility complex.</P>
<P>Yurika's plutonium updates, issued every 2-3 weeks, are excellent primers on
the MOX issue.</P>
<UL>
<LI>171 organizations/individuals <A HREF="russlttr.txt">worldwide sign letter
to President Clinton</A> urging rejection of MOX fuel option approved by Energy
Secretary Hazel O'Leary. January 14, 1997. <A HREF="moxprint.htm">Press release
for international letter,</A> 1/14/97.</LI>
<LI><A HREF="Moxalt.txt">DOE&nbsp;press conference 12/9/96 will announce
support for MOX option. Your letters, faxes and e-mails to DOE Secretary Hazel
O'Leary and to President Clinton are needed now!</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="Olearltr.htm">Letter from 14 national organizations to Hazel
O'Leary protesting MOX. 12/20/96</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="moxpr129.htm">NIRS, eight other groups express &quot;vigorous
opposition&quot; to MOX fuel proposal, 12/9/96</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="Congpu.txt">Eight Congressmembers write to President Clinton to
oppose MOX, 12/6/96</A></LI>
<LI>MOX means <A HREF="Ildump.txt">more plutonium in Illiniois' &quot;low-level&quot;
waste</A>. Press statement from NIRS, SECC, Greenpeace, 12/19/96.</LI>
