<HEAD>
   <TITLE>NIRS' Eastern European/NIS Project</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper1.gif">

<H2>Eastern Europe/NIS Project</H2>

<P>During 1997, NIRS will be extending its basic services to grassroots
environmental activists working in Eastern Europe and the Newly Independent
States. Activists in this region are usually underfunded, subject to repression
and suppression, and yet face perhaps the most dangerous nuclear menace
of all--a legacy of poorly-built and poorly-maintained Soviet nuclear reactors
and little, if any, radioactive waste management.</P>

<P>The activists in this area of the world work--often very effectively--against
great odds, with very few resources. It is NIRS' goal to supplement those
resources as much as we can. In many cases, the villains are now the same
as we face in the West: Westinghouse, Siemens, General Electric, Framatome--the
same companies that have threatened us all with nuclear meltdowns, cost
overruns, and a disrespect for openness and democracy. They now are jumping
on the Eastern bandwagon to &quot;upgrade&quot; or complete building hopeless
nuclear reactors. </P>

<P>We welcome your help in this new endeavor. We need volunteers in our
Washington office and elsewhere: translators, researchers, interns, and
others who can help. </P>

<P>Here you'll find selected files, grassroots publications, campaign updates,
and other information related to Eastern and NIS activities. Also check
out the International section of <A HREF="/htdocs/nirsbbs.htm">NIRSNET
on the Web </A>for much more on international anti-nuclear activities,
and use the <A HREF="http://www.nirs.org/$webboard/webb.exe">NIRS WebBoard</A>
for conversation, questions, and to keep up with each other.</P>

<P><A HREF="../../nirscamp.htm"><IMG SRC="nirslog2.gif"  ALIGN=BOTTOM></A></P>

</BODY>
</HTML>
