<HEAD>
   <TITLE>NIRS' Reactor Watchdog Project</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper1.gif">

<H2>NIRS Reactor Watchdog Project</H2>

<P>This project encompasses NIRS' work on nuclear reactor safety issues,
including reactor aging, use of ineffective Thermo-Lag fire barriers, containment
degradation and many more. Among this project's other current activities
are major campaigns to close the dangerous and uneconomical Haddam Neck
and Oyster Creek nuclear reactors. Here you'll find various NIRS and other
documents on these efforts. For more information about reactor-related
issues, check out our extensive files in the Reactor section of <A HREF="/htdocs/nirsbbs.htm">NIRSNET
on the Web.</A></P>

<P>On November 25, 1996, NIRS and the Citizens Awareness Network of Massachusetts
and Connecticut <A HREF="cypaper.htm">released a major report</A> detailing
the myriad of safety problems at Haddam Neck and called for the NRC to
revoke the reactor's operating license. </P>

<P>NIRS and CAN also released a <A HREF="cy2206.htm">formal petition</A>
to the NRC calling for revocation of Haddam Neck's license. 11/25/96.</P>

<P><A HREF="../../nirscamp.htm"><IMG SRC="nirslog2.gif" HEIGHT=58 WIDTH=130 ALIGN=BOTTOM></A></P>

</BODY>
