   <TITLE>linksus</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
   <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Preferred Customer">
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFBF0">

<H3>Link to other organizations working for a sustainable future. </H3>

<P><A HREF="http://www.citizen.org/CMEP/">Public Citizen's Critical Mass
Energy Project</A> Alerts, fact sheets, and lots of info. </P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.greenpeace.org">Greenpeace</A> The world's largest
and most important enivronmental organization. Alerts, articles, audio--it's
all here; one of the best websites of any kind anywhere. </P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.ucsusa.org">Union of Concerned Scientists</A> Info
on renewable energy, sustainable development, and more, from a scientific
perspective.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.essential.org/orgs/FOE/FOE.html">Friends of the
Earth</A> Varied environmental info, including the text of the Green Scissors
report--ways the U.S. can stop wasting taxpayer dollars on activites that
harm the environment.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.ratical.com/radiation/CNR/">Committee for Nuclear
Responsibility</A>. Actually, this site is run by the RatHaus, but it contains
the pioneering and essential work on radiation hazards conducted by Dr.
John Gofman. New pieces are added regularly.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.ieer.org">Institute for Energy and Environmental
Research.</A> Expert analysis and research on nuclear-related issues. And
don't miss a visit with Dr. Egghead!</P>

<P><A HREF="http://ecologia.nier.org">Ecologia</A> Especially interested
in Eastern European, former USSR issues. </P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.2020vision.org">20/20 Vision </A>Citizen activism.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org">IGC networks</A> Includes EcoNet, PeaceNet,
and more. Very comprehensive. </P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.envirolink.org/orgs/wardvalley">BAN Waste Ward Valley
home page</A>. Info on the proposed Ward Valley, California radioactive
waste dump, and how to stop it!</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.sfo.com/~rherried/welcome.htm">Abalone Alliance
website</A>. Lots of info on Ward Valley, plus renewable energy, nuclear
history and more.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://home.acadia.net/cbm/">Center for Biological Monitoring</A>
Interested in radiological monitoring and related issues, especially in
Maine.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/RWMA/">Radioactive Waste Management
Associates</A>. Technically a company, not a grassroots group (tho it consults
to many grassroots groups), but home to some of the most expert info on
radioactive waste anywhere.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://oraibi.alphadc.com/necona">National Environmental Coalition
of Native Americans</A>. Information on radioactive waste and transportation,
especially as it affects Native American communities. Lots of links to
Native American groups.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/redwood/">Redwood Alliance.</A> Lots
of info on nuclear issues and renewable energy from this veteran Northern
California organization.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.earthisland.org">Earth Island Institute.</A> This
organization is involved in just about everything, and so is their web
site. Read Earth Island Journal or check out the progress of any number
of environmental campaigns. </P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.downwinders.org">Downwinders.</A> Organization of
people who lived downwind of Nevada Test Site during above-ground nuclear
testing years. Site has info on nuclear and radiation issues.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://essential.org/freetheplanet/home.html">Free the Planet.</A>
Campus-based movement to &quot;confront corporate lawlessness and government
inaction through local, regional, and national action. Working on &quot;Webstock&quot;--web-based
activism November 1-4, 1996. FTP has been prominent in working to stop
the &quot;Mobile Chernobyl Act.&quot;</P>

<P>
<HR></P>

