<HEAD>
<TITLE>sustainable energy links</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Preferred Customer">
</HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFBF0">
<HR>
<H3>Link to sustainable energy-related sites</H3>
<P><A HREF="http://solstice.crest.org">Solstice</A> Just about everything you
wanted to know about energy efficiency and renewable energy. </P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.homepower.com">Home Power Magazine.</A> Small-scale
solar and other renewable energy design. If you ever wanted to learn how to
convert your home to solar power, this is the place. Lots of good links, too.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.iclei.org/co2">Cities for Climate Protection Campaign.</A>
Some 150 cities across the world, from Little Rock to Leipzig, have joined in
the Cities for Climate Protection Campaign. These cities will be trying to
improve energy efficiency and reduce fossil fuel use. This site provides info on
what cities are doing, how to get financing for improvements, and a lot more.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www/igc.apc.org/awea/">American Wind Energy Association.</A>
The trade organization of the U.S. wind energy industry. Lots of info on
windpower and the industry.</P>
<HR> 
<P><A HREF="nhome.htm"><IMG SRC="nirslog2.gif"></A></P> 
</BODY></HTML>
