<H1>Nuclear Reactors &amp; Nuclear Safety</H1>

<P>This area consists of numerous files relating to specific nuclear reactors
and to nuclear safety issues. Included are NRC policy (Secy) papers, transcripts
of NRC Commissioners' meetings, Generic Letters, and other relevant materials.
We may break this area down by reactor and safety issue in the future.
In the meantime, please use our <A HREF="reactorindex.htm">full-text indexing
and search capabilities</A> to find the file you wish, or just browse.</P>

<P>Other file areas of related interest include <A HREF="/fedreg/fdregbbs.htm">Federal
Register notices</A>, where you'll find notices of activities affecting
specific reactors; <A HREF="/dereg/decombbs.htm">deregulation and decommissioning</A>;
<A HREF="/nrcadmin/nrcadbbs.htm">NRC administrative</A> (files on NRC policymaking,
internal NRC activities, etc.; and <A HREF="/grassroots/grasbbs.htm">Dispatches
from the Grassroots</A>, includes newsletters, press statements and other
materials from local environmental activists.</P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+2>Recent Highlights</FONT></P>

<UL>
<LI>NRC inspection at <A HREF="R39676.txt">Dresden finds much more improvement
</A>is needed. 12/27/96.</LI>

<LI>Winds of change at NRC? Staff and Commission reject Nuclear Energy
Institute's fire protection petition, but will still recommend removing
fire protection regulations in favor of a more &quot;performance-based&quot;
approach. Released November 1996. <A HREF="S96-134y.txt">Staff memo</A>;
<A HREF="S96-134m.txt">Commissioners response</A>.</LI>

<LI>Briefing to NRC Commissioners on <A HREF="tr961016.txt">degradation
of containments at U.S. reactor</A>s. NRC staff says this is a growing
problem; lots of examples of serious rusting, crumbling of concrete, etc.
included here. October 17, 1996</LI>

<LI>NRC to send letter to nine nuclear plants asking about <A HREF="hq96145.txt">their
use of porous concrete</A> in containment construction, October 1996.</LI>

<LI>NRC says recent problems at <A HREF="Hq96133.txt">Maine Yankee</A>
are a result of cost-cutting at the utility--an increasingly frequent occurence
as utilities move toward deregulation. October 1996</LI>
</UL>

<P><A HREF="nirsbbs.htm"><IMG SRC="nirslog2.gif" HEIGHT=58 WIDTH=130 ALIGN=BOTTOM></A></P>

