<H1>
<HR width="100%">WebFind Form</H1>

<P>You can use this form to search for documents in the High-Level Waste
library. You can use 'and' and 'or' between your keywords, as well as &quot;not&quot;;
'and' applies by default. Try to be as focused in your choice of keywords
as possible; for example, the words 'radioactive' or 'waste' are unlikely
to lead to a productive search. Try, for example, dry and cask, or onsite,
or Yucca Mountain, instead. </P>

