<H1>Federal Register Notices</H1>

<P>
<HR></P>

<P>This area consists of Federal Register notices related to nuclear power,
radioactive waste and other related issues. Often these provide opportunities
for you to ACT! So, send in your comments, demand public hearings, and
let's try to bring a little democracy to nuclear issues...</P>

<P>Recent highlights are listed here. This file area is fully indexed.
You can search by date, utility, reactor, or any other way that seems appropriate.
<A HREF="fedindex.htm">Click here to use the index.</A></P>

<P><B><FONT SIZE=+2>Recent Highlights</FONT></B></P>

<P><B>DOE proposed rule on <A HREF="de1696pr.txt">general guidelines for
the recommendation of sites for a high-level waste</A> dump. This is extremely
important--it is meant to attempt to remove essential siting criteria (such
as transportation impacts, etc.) from consideration for decision on Yucca
Mountain dump. 60-day public comment period (although extension has been
applied for) ends February 16, 1997. Comment today!</B></P>

<P><B>NRC <A HREF="se2396ur.txt">draft policy statement on utility restructuring
and deregulation</A>. Up for public comment until December 9, 1996. Note
that the statement does not address nuclear safety issues--it should! 9/23/96</B></P>

<P><B>NRC certifies <A HREF="se1996us.txt">U.S. Enrichment Corp. plants</A>,
9/19/96. </B></P>

<P><B>NRC order establishing <A HREF="au2096nu.txt">independent corrective
action plan for Northeast Utilities</A>' very troubled three-unit Millstone
reactor complex. 8/20/96.</B></P>

<P><B>DOE <A HREF="jl11p6mo.txt">arrangement with Japan</A>, re: MOX fuel,
7/11/96.</B></P>

<P><B>DOE <A HREF="jl1096do.txt">plutonium stabilization plan</A>, 7/10/96.</B></P>

<P><A HREF="nirsbbs.htm"><IMG SRC="nirslog2.gif" HEIGHT=58 WIDTH=130 ALIGN=BOTTOM></A></P>

