<HEAD>
   <TITLE>decommissioning and deregulation</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#FFF0F0" BGCOLOR="#008080" LINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#0000FF">

<P><IMG SRC="nirsweb.gif" HEIGHT=60 WIDTH=300 ALIGN=BOTTOM> 
<HR></P>

<H1>Decommissioning and Deregulation </H1>

<P>This area includes files on the decommissioning of nuclear reactors
and other atomic facilities, and on the deregulation of radioactive waste.
At first blush, these areas may seem unrelated. However, they are in fact
inextricably tied: the nuclear power industry and the Nuclear Regulatory
Commission see deregulation (declaring a certain level of radiation &quot;safe&quot;
or &quot;acceptable&quot; and thus not requiring regulatory oversight)
as the essential key to allowing cheap decommissioning of nuclear facilities.
Once a level of radiation is accepted as &quot;safe,&quot; the way is clear
for further deregulation of radioactive materials--for example, in consumer
products, as regular garbage, etc. The NRC has from time to time proposed
just such a deregulation policy (last time it was called &quot;below regulatory
concern&quot; and was revoked by Congress in 1992 following a national
grassroots citizens uprising). The NRC is now seeking new ways to implement
a deregulation policy, through decommissioning standards. Because deregulation
policies benefit only the nuclear industry--obviously the public receives
no benefit from increased exposure to radioactive materials--they remain
quite controversial.</P>

<P>Here you will find files on a variety of decommissioning and deregulation
issues. For related information, see <A HREF="../../llw/llwbbs.htm">&quot;low-level&quot;
radioactive waste</A>, <A HREF="../../hlw/hlwbbs.htm">high-level radioactive
waste</A>, <A HREF="/reactor/reacbbs.htm">reactor safety</A>, and <A HREF="/radiation/radbbs.htm">radiation</A>.
For a grassroots perspective, check out <A HREF="/grassroots/grasbbs.htm">Dispatches
from the Grassroots</A>. </P>

<P>This file area is fully indexed. To search this file area, <A HREF="decomindex.htm">click
here.</A></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+2>Recent Highlights</FONT></P>

<UL>
<LI>Transcript of Commissioners' <A HREF="Tr961007.txt">briefing on Site&nbsp;Management
Decommissioning Plan</A>, which covers thousands of fuel cycle and other
non-reactor sites across the country, 10/7/96.</LI>

<LI>NRC <A HREF="sy96200.txt">policy statement on &quot;reuse &amp; recycling&quot;
of radioactive materials</A>. Here comes BRC again! Read and respond. Sept.
1996.</LI>

<LI>Final rule on <A HREF="sy96086.txt">decommissioning procedures for
reactors</A>. Utilities no longer need submit a decommissioning plan in
advance. June 1996 (note: file is 260k)</LI>
</UL>

<P><A HREF="nirsbbs.htm"><IMG SRC="nirslog2.gif" HEIGHT=58 WIDTH=130></A></P>

