<H1>Fuel Cycle Facilities</H1>

<P>
<HR></P>

<P>This file area includes documents relating to fuel cycle facilities:
uranium enrichment, processing and fuel fabrication plants. These are among
the most polluting plants of any kind in the U.S. They are regulated (poorly)
by the Nuclear Regulatory Commission, but are allowed to release significantly
more radiation than are nuclear reactors or waste dumps. These files are
fully indexed. You may search by company, topic (i.e. centrifuges) or just
about any other way.</P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+3>Recent Highlights</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Uranium hexaflouride <A HREF="R39673.txt">release at Allied
Signal plant</A>, 12/18/96.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>NRC Licensing Board rules Louisiana Energy Services is
<A HREF="lesdec.txt">financially unqualified to build</A> uranium enrichment
plant. It's the beginning of the end for LES! Decision file is 197k. 12/4/96</FONT></P>
<FONT SIZE=+1></FONT>
<P><A HREF="cycleindex.htm">Click here to use the index.</A></P>

<P><A HREF="nirsbbs.htm"><IMG SRC="nirslog2.gif" HEIGHT=58 WIDTH=130 ALIGN=BOTTOM></A></P>

