<H1>NRC Administrative Files</H1>

<P>
<HR></P>

<P>This is kind of a catch-all file area. It includes documents relating
to how the NRC does things (i.e. inspects reactors, sets safety goals,
etc.), as well as to matters like personnel changes, general speeches by
NRC personnel, etc. If you didn't find what you were looking for elsewhere,
you may well find it here. These files are fully indexed. </P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+2>Recent Highlights</FONT></P>

<P>Major <A HREF="Hq96172.txt">shake-up and restructuring at NRC</A>. Taylor
is out, Callan is in... 12/4/96</P>

<P>List and <A HREF="sy96176.txt">discussion of upcoming NRC rulemakings</A>.
Useful for knowing what you can expect over next year or so. Released October
21, 1996. (232k)</P>

<P>Transcript of NRC &quot;All-Employees Day&quot; sessions, where NRC
employees get to quiz the Commissioners about agency policies. Best question,
from an administrative law judge: why does NRC constantly seem to do everything
possible to limit meaningful public participation? <A HREF="tr10176a.txt">Morning
session</A>; <A HREF="tr10176b.txt">afternoon session</A>; October 17,
1996</P>

<P>Speech by <A HREF="sph9612.txt">NRC Commissioner Kenneth Rogers to Westinghouse
</A>on future of NRC regulation. He criticizes New England utilities (and
industry generally) for trying to find legal bases for not providing information
to NRC, rather than being open. June 12, 1996</P>

