<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Toolbox: International</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
   <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Preferred Customer">
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<H1>THE NIRS TOOLBOX</H1>

<P>
<HR></P>

<H4>Human history becomes more and more a race between education and catastrophe.
~ H.G. Wells</H4>

<P>A ~ indicates that this Toolbox entry contains information relevant
to the health effects of low-dose and/or long-term exposure to radiation.
</P>

<H4>There are two ways to order materials from the NIRS&nbsp;toolbox:</H4>

<H4>1. The fast way: fax your order to NIRS at 202-462-2183. Include your
Visa, Mastercard or Discover Card number, expiration date, and signature.
</H4>

<H4>2. The slow way: mail to NIRS at 1424 16th Street NW, #404, Washington
DC 20036. Please make your check payable to NIRS. Thank you.</H4>

<P>Unfortunately, due to problems collecting payment on invoiced orders,
all orders must now be prepaid (we're not a collection agency after all,
we're an environmental group...)</P>

<H2>INTERNATIONAL</H2>

<P><B>I-4000</B> $1.20 12pp Summer 1986 </P>

<P>&quot;Commercial Nuclear Power in Western Europe: Experience and Prospects&quot;
</P>

<P>David Hart, FARPP </P>

<P>Detailed overview on all aspects of fuel cycle. </P>

<P><B>I-4001</B> $1.80 18pp 1991 </P>

<P>Crisis in the French Nuclear Industry </P>

<P>Francois Nectoux, Greenpeace </P>

<P>This report explores the impact of nuclear power on the French economy,
including increasing production and building costs. It claims that France's
almost total dependence (80%) on nuclear energy is unhealthy. </P>

<P><B>I-6000</B> $.90 9pp 2/86 </P>

<P>&quot;Nuclear Power Development and Management&quot; </P>

<P>Maxim Rylsky, Soviet Life </P>

<P>Feature on nuclear power in the Soviet Union. Includes interviews with
residents and workers at Chernobyl prior to the accident. A very interesting
piece retrospectively. </P>

<P><B>I-7000</B> $.40 4pp 1983 </P>

<P>&quot;The Myth of CANDU&quot; </P>

<P>Paul McKay </P>

<P>Canadian researcher shatters the myth that Canadian heavy-water reactors
are problem-free compared to US light-water reactors. </P>

<P><B>I-8000</B> $.60 6pp 12/88 </P>

<P>&quot;Plutonium for All: Leaks in Global Safeguards&quot; </P>

<P>Richard Bolt, Bulletin of Atomic Scientists </P>

<P>Even if the IAEA met its own inspection goals, the theft of a bomb's
worth of plutonium could easily go unnoticed. </P>

<P><A HREF="toolhome.htm"><IMG SRC="nirslog2.gif" HEIGHT=58 WIDTH=130></A>
</P>

</BODY>
