<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Toolbox: TMI</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
   <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Preferred Customer">
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<H1>THE NIRS TOOLBOX</H1>

<P>
<HR></P>

<H4>Human history becomes more and more a race between education and catastrophe.
~ H.G. Wells</H4>

<P>A ~ indicates that this Toolbox entry contains information relevant
to the health effects of low-dose and/or long-term exposure to radiation.
</P>

<H4>There are two ways to order materials from the NIRS&nbsp;toolbox:</H4>

<H4>1. The fast way: fax your order to NIRS at 202-462-2183. Include your
Visa, Mastercard or Discover Card number, expiration date, and signature.
</H4>

<H4>2. The slow way: mail to NIRS at 1424 16th Street NW, #404, Washington
DC 20036. Please make your check payable to NIRS. Thank you.</H4>

<H4>Unfortunately, due to problems collecting payment on invoiced orders,
all orders must now be prepaid (we're not a collection agency after all,
we're an environmental group...)</H4>

<P>
<HR></P>

<H2>THREE MILE ISLAND</H2>

<P><B>PTMI-2000</B> $1.40 14pp 5/87-6/87 </P>

<P>&quot;Three Mile Island Did It&quot; </P>

<P>Harvey Wasserman, Harrowsmith </P>

<P>Eight years later, a comprehensive survey of the damage caused by the
TMI accident. Includes interviews with residents and scientists, addresses
the question of accuracy regarding the original estimates of radiation
hazards. </P>

<P><B>PTMI-2001</B> $3.70 37pp 1989/1994 </P>

<P>&quot;A Decade of Delay, Deceit and Danger: TMI 1979-1989 A Retrospective
</P>

<P>Joanne Doroshow, Three Mile Island Alert </P>

<P>This is a good overview, highlighted with specific cases, of the TMI
accident. Health effects, plant operation, and NRC &quot;regulation&quot;
are all discussed as well as a timeline of important events. A very good
report with a 15th anniversary update (March, 1994). </P>

<P><B>PTMI-3000</B> $.60 6pp 1989-1990 </P>

<P>&quot;The NRC's TMI Action Plan: A Case Study of Regulatory Failure&quot;
</P>

<P>NIRS, Groundswell </P>

<P>This article tells why the NRC's attempt to incorporate the lessons
learned at TMI have failed. </P>

<P><B>PTMI-3001</B> $.50 5 pp 5/87 </P>

<P>Interview With Julian Greenspun, Former Deputy Chief of Litigation,
Criminal Division, Department of Justice, Corporate Crime Reporter </P>

<P>During this interview, Greenspun contends that the NRC was responsible
for covering up various safety risks at TMI before and after the accident.
</P>

<P><B>PTMI-4000</B> $1.70 17pp 6/80 </P>

<P>&quot;The Silent Toll'' </P>

<P>Thomas Pawlick, Harrowsmith </P>

<P>Profile of Dr. Ernest Sternglass and his examination of effects of TMI
radiation releases. Excellent non-technical introduction to issue. </P>

<P><B>PTMI-4001</B> $3.20 32pp 11/82 </P>

<P>Three Mile Island Revisited </P>

<P>Katagiri and Smith </P>

<P>Two in-depth stories discuss the lives of two TMI survivors and the
silence among most of the scientific and medical communities concerning
the health effects of the accident. </P>

<P><B>PTMI-4002</B> $3.50 35 pp 3/3/83 </P>

<P>Presentation by Mitsuri Katagiri and Aileen Smith Katagiri </P>

<P>The Katagiris recount five of the over 200 local anecdotes and strange
occurrences subsequent to the accident that health and government officials
refused to investigate. </P>

<P><B>PTMI-4003</B> $3.20 32 pp 6/21/84 </P>

<P>Aamodt's Motion Before the NRC Commissioners </P>

<P>This statement contains an abridged version of the Aamodt study and
several accompanying affidavits, along with a sample interview questionnaire
and representative Reed's letter to NRC. </P>

<P><B>PTMI-4004</B> $1.30 13pp 3/89 </P>

<P>&quot;In the Valley of the Shadow of Three Mile Island&quot; </P>

<P>Joyce Hollyday, Sojourners </P>

<P>Ten years after the nation's worst commercial nuclear accident, a controversy
rages that has implications for the health, safety and future of us all.
</P>

<P><B>PTMI-4005</B> $.60 6pp 10/6/86 </P>

<P>&quot;Three Mile Island: What Really Happened to the People Who Live
There&quot; </P>

<P>Joyce Maynard US </P>

<P>A powerful investigative piece on the wide spread health problems in
the areas around the TMI reactor. </P>

<P><B>PTMI-4006</B> $.30 3pp 9/90 </P>

<P>&quot;TMI, NCI Studies Give Industry Clean Bill of Health, Or Do They?&quot;
</P>

<P>NIRS, The Nuclear Monitor </P>

<P>This article critiques the health impact studies of TMI and on nuclear
power plant operation in general. </P>

<P><B>PTMI-5000</B> $.30 3 pp 1979 </P>

<P>Statement of President Carter on the Kemeny Commission Report </P>

<P>USNRC 1979 Annual Report </P>

<P>In his statement, the former president calls nuclear power an energy
source of last resort. He emphasizes some then current reasons why the
door on nuclear power must remain open, but also stresses the need to develop
alternative energy sources. This commission report was a result of the
TMI accident. </P>

<P><B>PTMI-5001</B> $.80 8pp 3/89-4/89 </P>

<P>&quot;Ten Years of Fallout&quot; </P>

<P>Christopher Flavin, WorldWatch Magazine </P>

<P>Lessons of the TMI accident and the problem with the new generation
of reactors. </P>

<P><B>PTMI-5002</B> $4.10 41 pp 7/23/79 </P>

<P>Comments by Admiral Rickover, USN </P>

<P>Admiral Rickover President's Commission </P>

<P>Rickover, then director of the naval nuclear propulsion program, comments
on safe procedures for running a nuclear facility. He was asked to comment
by the special Presidential Commission convened to investigate the TMI
accident. Also included is a notarized letter from his daughter-in-law
stating he told her the government suppressed the seriousness of the accident.
</P>

<P><B>PTMI-7000</B> $.20 2pp 1/26/88 </P>

<P>&quot;Three Mile Island Cleanup Uncovers New Details&quot; </P>

<P>Walter Sullivan, New York Times </P>

<P>As cleanup continues, new evidence supports claims that the accident
was worse than originally thought. </P>

<P><B>PTMI-7001</B> $2.00 20pp 2/10/85-2/12/85 </P>

<P>&quot;Three Mile Island: Accident Without End&quot; </P>

<P>Jim Detjan and Susan FitzGerald, Philadelphia Inquirer </P>

<P>Excellent series detailing worker contamination during the TMI cleanup,
and GPU's mistreatment of whistleblowers. </P>

<P><A HREF="toolhome.htm"><IMG SRC="nirslog2.gif" HEIGHT=58 WIDTH=130></A>
</P>

</BODY>
</HTML>
