<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Toolbox: Uranium</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
   <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Preferred Customer">
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<H1>THE NIRS TOOLBOX</H1>

<P>
<HR></P>

<H4>Human history becomes more and more a race between education and catastrophe.
~ H.G. Wells</H4>

<P>A ~ indicates that this Toolbox entry contains information relevant
to the health effects of low-dose and/or long-term exposure to radiation.
</P>

<H4>There are two ways to order materials from the NIRS&nbsp;toolbox:</H4>

<H4>1. The fast way: fax your order to NIRS at 202-462-2183. Include your
Visa, Mastercard or Discover Card number, expiration date, and signature.
</H4>

<H4>2. The slow way: mail to NIRS at 1424 16th Street NW, #404, Washington
DC 20036. Please make your check payable to NIRS. Thank you.</H4>

<H4>Unfortunately, due to problems collecting payment on invoiced orders,
all orders must now be prepaid (we're not a collection agency after all,
we're an environmental group...)</H4>

<P>
<HR></P>

<H2>URANIUM</H2>

<P><B>UR-2000</B> $1.20 12pp 12/79 </P>

<P>&quot;Uranium Mining and Milling: A Primer.&quot; </P>

<P>SRIC, The Workbook </P>

<P>Excellent overview of technology, environmental and health impacts,
and regulatory process. </P>

<P><B>UR-2001</B> $1.70 17pp Spring 1991 </P>

<P>&quot;Uranium Mining at the Grand Canyon&quot; </P>

<P>Cate Gilles, et al., The Workbook </P>

<P>The author focuses on uranium mining in the Grand Canyon region and
how it affects the Havasupai and Hualapai from a health and cultural standpoint.
It also investigates the effect on the environment and industry claims
that it will not be adversely affected. </P>

<P><B>UR-2002</B> $4.20 42pp 10/92 </P>

<P>Uranium Mining in Northem Saskatchewan-ls It Worth the Risk? </P>

<P>Jamie Kneen, Campaign for Nuclear Phaseout </P>

<P>This collection of fact sheets explores all topics of Saskatchewan mining
from health risks to environmental risks. Air and water quality and tailings
management are reviewed as well as McClean and Cluff Lakes environmental
impacts statements. </P>

<P><B>UR-2003</B> $1.70 17pp 7/85-9/85 </P>

<P>&quot;The 'Costs' of Uranium: Who's Paying with Lives, Lands, and Dollars&quot;
</P>

<P>SRIC, The Workbook </P>

<P>Most recent look at uranium mining, as companies, workers, and citizens
come to grips with uranium mill tailings. </P>

<P><B>UR-3000</B> $2.30 23pp </P>

<P>A collection of documents regarding the Kerr-McGee facility in Gore,
OK </P>

<P>Pat Costner </P>

<P>Ms. Costner details radiation exposure to workers and the public after
the Jan 1986 explosion which killed one worker. She also describes soil
and water contamination. Also included is an informal cancer survey of
the surrounding area. </P>

<P><B>UR-3001</B> $.50 5pp Spring 1990 </P>

<P>&quot;Uranium Enrichment Plant Battle is First of Second Nuclear Generation&quot;
</P>

<P>NIRS, Groundswell </P>

<P>This story highlights the antics of Senator Bennett Johnston (D-La)
concerning Louisiana Energy Services Uranium Enrichment Plant and the resulting
community action. LES is attempting to construct this plant in a poverty-stricken,
mostly African American neighborhood. </P>

<P><B>UR-3002</B> $7.70 77pp 1/94 </P>

<P>Comments on the DEIS for Louisiana Energy Services </P>

<P>NIRS, Sierra Club Legal Defense Fund </P>

<P>These three publications include a NIRS Draft Environmental Impact Statement
fact sheet regarding the proposed LES reprocessing site in Homer, Louisiana,
and comments by both NIRS and Sierra Club Legal Defense Fund voicing concerns
that the DEIS was mishandled. </P>

<P><B>UR-3003</B> $.60 6pp 1/94-2/94 </P>

<P>&quot;The Dirty History of Nuclear Power: The Sequoyah Fuels Story&quot;
</P>

<P>Conger Beasley, Jr., E the Environmental Magazine </P>

<P>Article which recounts the struggles of native peoples against Sequoyah
Fuels, one of the most careless and arrogant uranium refineries. </P>

<P><B>UR-3004</B> $3.70 37pp 9/28/93 </P>

<P>Silent Sirens: Another Sequoyah Fuels Accident </P>

<P>Lance Hughes and Diane Curran, NACE </P>

<P>Details yet another Sequoyah Fuels accident (November 17, 1992) and
exposes the misconduct of the EPA NRC, and SFC. </P>

<P><A HREF="toolhome.htm"><IMG SRC="nirslog2.gif" HEIGHT=58 WIDTH=130></A>
</P>

</BODY>
