<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Toolbox: Other Sources of Info</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
   <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Preferred Customer">
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<H1>THE NIRS TOOLBOX</H1>

<P>
<HR></P>

<H4>Human history becomes more and more a race between education and catastrophe.
~ H.G. Wells</H4>

<P>A ~ indicates that this Toolbox entry contains information relevant
to the health effects of low-dose and/or long-term exposure to radiation.
</P>

<H4>There are two ways to order materials from the NIRS&nbsp;toolbox:</H4>

<H4>1. The fast way: fax your order to NIRS at 202-462-2183. Include your
Visa, Mastercard or Discover Card number, expiration date, and signature.
</H4>

<H4>2. The slow way: mail to NIRS at 1424 16th Street NW, #404, Washington
DC 20036. Please make your check payable to NIRS. Thank you.</H4>

<H4>Unfortunately, due to problems collecting payment on invoiced orders,
all orders must now be prepaid (we're not a collection agency after all,
we're an environmental group...)</H4>

<P>
<HR></P>

<H2>RENEWABLE AND EFFICIENCY INFORMATION AVAILABLE FROM OTHER ORGANIZATIONS</H2>

<P>Directory of Industry Members-with a directory of the U.S. Wind Industry.
Available from the American Wind Energy Association. Call 202-383-2500
or write: 777 N. Capitol Street, NE, Washington, DC 20002. </P>

<P>Cool Energy: Renewable Solutions to Environmental Problems. by Michael
Brower, 1992. and Powering the Midwest: Renewable Electricity for the Economy
and the Environment., 1993. Available from the Union of Concerned Scientists.
Call 617-547-5552 or write: 2 Brattle Square, Cambridge, MA 02238 for further
information. </P>

<P>Renewable Energy Sourcebook. updated annually. Available from Public
Citizen Critical Mass Energy Project. Call 202-588-1000 or write: 1600
20th Street, NW, Washington, DC 20009 for details. </P>

<P>Sustainable Energy. Available from Renew America at 202-232-2252, 1400
16th Street, NW, Washington, DC 20036. $5.00 plus $.75 postage and handling.
</P>

<P>Energy Directions and other publications. Available from the Center
for the Study of Responsive Law. PO Box 19367, Washington, DC 20036. $6.00
including shipping and handling, prepayment required. </P>

<P>
<HR></P>

<P>Available from Worldwatch Institute, Call 202-452-1999 or write: 1776
Massachusetts Avenue, NW, Washington, DC 20036: </P>

<P>&quot;Powering the Future: Blueprint for a Sustainable Electricity Industry&quot;
by Christopher Flavin. World Watch Paper 119, June 1994. </P>

<P>&quot;Reassessing Nuclear Power: The Fallout from Chernobyl,&quot; by
Christopher Flavin. World Watch Paper 75, March 1987. </P>

<P>&quot;Nuclear Waste: The Problem that Won't Go Away, Nicholas Lenssen.
World Watch Paper 106, December 1991. </P>

<P>&quot;Beyond the Petroleum Age: Designing a Solar Economy,&quot; by
