<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Greenpeace Ukraine demonstration</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>GREENPEACE UKRAINE BLOCKS ENTRANCE TO UKRAINIAN WHITE HOUSE TO DEMAND
SHUTDOWN OF REMAINING CHERNOBYL REACTORS</H2>
<P><STRONG>KIEV, APRIL 22, 1996</STRONG></P>
<P>At the top left, two policemen attempt to block Greenpeace Ukraine
protestors from reaching the Presidential offices. Undeterred, demonstrators
bypass police by running up the hill. <A HREF="gp1.jpg">Photo</A> (139k)</P>
<P>Having run in from three locations, more than 70 Greenpeace Ukraine
activists block the doors to the Ukrainian White House. They are delivering a
coffin with a model of the Chernobyl sarcophagus inside. Each has brought a
cross representing a village that has been permanently dislocated due to
Chernobyl. <A HREF="gp2.jpg">Photo </A>(172k)</P>
<P>An emissay of Ukraine's President Kuchma argued that Chernobyl is safe, and
that Greenpeace is not &quot;expert.&quot; The Greenpeace spokesman presented
the emissary with a letter demanding immediate shutdown of the remaining
Chernobyl reactors.</P>
<P>All at once, the people on the steps rose and began surrounding Kuchma's
agent with crosses. As TV cameras focused in, and the Greenpeace spokesman
stepped back, the Ukrainian official found himself surrounded by the crosses
brought by an abandoned generation. <A HREF="gp3.jpg">Photo</A> (156k)</P>
