<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Chernobyl resources</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY><H1>Resources on Chernobyl</H1>
<P>This site will include a variety of resources on the Chernobyl disaster and
its aftermath. NGOs, grassroots groups, and non-profit groups generally are
welcome to submit their items for inclusion on this site. Send text files in
ASCII text and graphics in gif format to nirsnet @aol.com or nirsnet@igc.apc.org
or send disks in above formats or htm to NIRS, 1424 16th Street NW, #601,
Washington, DC 2036. NIRS will review all materials before posting; however,
posting does not imply endorsement from NIRS nor the No More Chernobyls steering
committee. Books, reports, research papers, and other materials are all welcome.
For-profit entities wishing to submit items for this site should call Michael
Mariotte at 202-328-0002 before sending materials.</P>
<HR><IMG SRC="nebbook.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" HSPACE="1">
<P>Chernobyl: The Forbidden Truth. A new book by journalist and member of
President Yeltsin's Council Alla Yaroshinskaya. Foreward by Dr. John Gofman;
introduction by professor David Marples. Published by University of Nebraska
Press, 1995. <A HREF="nebbook.htm">More information.</A></P>
